title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in butter.
Combine orange rind, orange juice and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Fold in coarsely chopped cranberries, nuts and vanilla.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes (or until done).
Slices best the next day.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all but soup and water.
Make into meat balls and brown in skillet.
Drain.
Stir soup in meat drippings until brown.
Add water.
Mix well.
Add meat balls.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: asian chicken salad
directions: Preheat broiler.
Combine soy sauce, lemon juice, sesame oil, garlic and ginger in a small bowl.
Place red pepper and chicken on broiler pan 3 inches from heat.
Broil chicken, 3 minutes per side, until opaque.
Broil pepper until skin is black, turning, about 10 minutes.
Place pepper in brown paper bag until cool; peel, core, seed and slice into strips.
Slice chicken into strips.
Toss with pepper, noodles and sauce.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: skillet barbecued pork chops
directions: In large skillet with
a tight fitting lid, brown chops in oil about 5 minutes
to
each
side.
Drain off excess fat. Sprinkle celery, brown
sugar,
lemon
juice
and
seasonings evenly over chops.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover, simmer over low heat 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan combine sugar,

flour, salt, cocoa, and egg yolks; stir in enough milk to make good paste. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes; gradually adding remaining milk. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Pour into cooled baked pastry shell. Spread meringue on top of pie and bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: pralinies
directions: Microwave first 5 ingredients on High for 12 minutes, stirring at 4 minutes.
Add baking powder to mixture, then cook on High for 1 minutes.
Beat until sticky, drop on foil.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until cool.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add pasta or macaroni and mix well.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tea for 50
directions: Make syrup of water and sugar.
Cool and add juices to tea. Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice in tall glasses.
Garnish with fresh mint.
The base may be frozen.
Before serving, let base thaw partially and serve with ginger ale and mint.

title: mock eclair dessert
directions: Boil water and margarine.
Add flour and stir until it leaves side of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time beating by hand until mixed. Spread in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 450° until crust is nice and brown.
Finish baking at 375°.
Shake to tell when done.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Cube steak and cut into 4 x 6-inch pieces.
On each piece, put 2 slices of raw bacon, 4 thin slices of carrots, 4 thin slices of green pepper and a few pieces of onion.
Roll up, tie with string and roll in flour.
Salt and pepper.
Brown all sides.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Blend all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed for 1 minute. Don't overmix.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: smoothie
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients. Cover and process until smooth. Pour and serve immediately. Diabetic exchange - 1 fruit, 1 milk.
Makes 3 servings, 161 calories each.

title: banana split pie
directions: Place grahams in 13 x 9-inch pan and drizzle with melted oleo.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Pour your milk in a mixing bowl.
Add your lemonade and stir until well mixed.
Then add the Cool Whip, then mix with a big mixing spoon, lightly combining.
Pour into the pie shell.
Chill. Makes four servings.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries well.
Let stand on paper towels.
Combine butter, syrup and salt; stir in sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Chill if too soft.
Shape about 1 teaspoon of mixture around each cherry. Place on wax paper lined pan.
Chill.
In deep bowl over pan of hot water, melt chocolate coating.
Stir constantly.
Do not add any liquid.
Holding onto stems, dip cherries, one at a time, into melted mixture.
Spoon over cherries to coat.
Place back on waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator to harden.
Store covered in a cool place.
Let ripen for a week or two, so fondant will begin to liquefy.
Makes 60 covered cherries.

title: sausage upside-down cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onion and green pepper in a skillet until sausage is brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour, tomato paste, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese and olives.
Spread evenly in 9-inch square pan.

title: base frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter, milk and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat with mixer.
Add more milk 1 teaspoon at a time.
Should be thin.

title: chili
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Pour in tomato juice.
Add cumin, chili powder and sugar.
(Chili powder can be adjusted to suit taste.)
Add the 3 cans of beans.
Let simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken without skin and debone.
Cook broccoli and spread on bottom of buttered dish.
In another bowl, combine chicken, soups and mushrooms; pour over broccoli.
Prepare stuffing mix and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in large bowl.
Microwave on Medium (50% power) until chocolate chips melt, 3 to 5 minutes. Stir once or twice during cooking.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in well greased dish, 8 x 8-inches.
Refrigerate.

title: "jersey devil" clams
directions: Simmer clams in juice for 5 minutes.
Cook onion, green pepper, celery and celery leaves in a little butter until tender. Combine with thyme, pepper, mustard and bread crumbs.
Mix well with clams.
Grease clam shells, fill with mixture and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Set to the side. Mix eggs, whipping cream and pimento peppers together. Divide sausage and place into uncooked pie crusts. Place cheese over sausage and pour egg, whipping cream and pimento pepper mixture over sausage and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put one layer of potatoes, then one layer onions.
Do this until onions and potatoes are used up. Then put 2 cans cream of chicken in a pot with 2 cans water.
Heat and pour over pork chops, potatoes and onions. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: fried m'hammer chicken(enough for 2 chickens, about 3 pounds each)
directions: Put the whole chickens in a thick-bottomed saucepan with the offal.

Cover with 2 big glassfuls of water; add salt, butter, crushed garlic, whole onion, paprika, cumin and the small bunch of coriander, which should be removed when the chicken is cooked. Cook with the lid on over a moderate heat, turning the chickens over from time to time so that they are well impregnated with the sauce.
Add water if necessary.
Take the onion out as soon as it is cooked and put on one side.

When the chickens are cooked, i.e., the flesh comes away from the bones easily between the fingers, mash the onion with a small piece of chicken liver either in an electric blender or in a vegetable sieve.
Mix a teaspoonful of flour with the liver and onion and then add this to the saucepan.
Check the seasoning and remove the saucepan from the heat as soon as the sauce has thickened.
Twenty minutes before serving, heat 100 g (4 ounces) of butter and a ladleful of oil in a pan and fry the chickens golden brown all over.
Arrange on a hot dish.
Reheat the chicken sauce without letting it boil away. Add 2 soupspoonfuls of the frying fat, stirring the saucepan with a circular stirring movement and pour over the chicken.
Serve at once.

title: peanut butter hugs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with Hershey's Hugs.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Put in pineapple; over that, spread pie filling.
If you like coconut, spread on filling, then spread cake mix on top.
Melt butter and pour over top of dry cake mix.
Bake 20 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello, boiling water and sugar until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Stir, then add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: grams plum pudding
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift together flour (resift), soda, baking powder, cinnamon and spices.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in chopped fruit and nuts.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt baking chocolate and butter or margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla; combine well.
Dissolve cornstarch in the milk; add this to the other ingredients and stir over medium heat until thickening begins.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain the sauerkraut 15 minutes in a colander.
Cut with scissors into 1-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cover and store in the refrigerator for 24 hours. The salad will store indefinitely.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix in a boiler the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil under moderate heat.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats, peanut butter and pecans.
Stir together well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Let dry.
They are ready to eat.
Enjoy.

title: cut glass salad
directions: Dissolve orange, cherry and lime Jell-O separately, each in 1 cup boiling water.
Congeal and cut into cubes.
Next, dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and cool.
Stir in sour cream, pecans and drained crushed pineapple.
Fold in Jell-O cubes and mix until colors are distributed.
Pour into mold and congeal. Use mayonnaise to grease mold.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in chocolate syrup. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in flour.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: my sister's special cornbread
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan and place in a 450° oven while preparing cornbread. Combine dry ingredients. Mix wet ingredients well and pour into dry ingredients, stirring until lumps are just barely removed. Pour into hot pan. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix jello and cake mix.
Add water, berries and Wesson oil. Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back to touch.

title: italian broccoli salad
directions: Crumble bacon; cut flower heads into small pieces.
Peel stems and slice.
Combine with other ingredients.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix together and freeze for 24 hours.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.
Mix with large bottle of 7-Up.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute chopped celery and onion in margarine until soft. Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 min.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Brown roast. Add water (about 1 1/2 cups). Cover and simmer slowly until well done. Remove pork and shred, removing fat and bone. Cool broth in which it was cooked. Remove fat from top and use 1 cup of remaining liquid. Combine pork liquid, catsup and other ingredients and mix well. Simmer slowly for 3 hours.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, putting 1 cup of nuts to the side.
Mix well and shape into one ball.
Place on center of dish, flattening bottom.
Put cup of nuts on outside of ball.
Chill for one hour.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: no cook candy balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, walnuts and butter in mixing bowl.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll each ball in coconut. Chill.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix crackers and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with candy. Refrigerate.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Stir flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda and cinnamon together.
Add carrots, undrained pineapple, oil, coconut and eggs; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: baked pears with pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine raisins and hazelnuts in a food processor or blender and process until finely chopped. With the motor running, add honey and cheese.
Continue to process until a soft ball forms. Spoon cheese mixture into cavities of the pears and set them in an ovenproof casserole.
Pour juice around them and bake until pears are tender (about 35 minutes).
Serve hot as a dessert, breakfast or snack.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger tater tot hot dish
directions: Put hamburger in baking dish.
Add salt to taste and onion. Put Tater Tots over meat.
Spread soup over entire mixture.
Do not add liquid to soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meringue mints
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with brown paper. Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar and continue to beat on high until stiff peaks are formed.
Fold in mint extract, food coloring and chocolate chips.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, milk and salt together.
Melt the butter in pan (and sides).
Pour in flour mixture, then add peaches.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mrs. roby's white sugar cookies
directions: You must use an old coffee cup and a regular teaspoon for measuring.
Must use lard.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter. Bake in moderate oven about 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This is an old fashion recipe.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Put
jello
in
a
large bowl and add 2 cups of boiling water; stir to dissolve gelatin.
Cool to room temperature and add
cream cheese
(softened)
with the pineapple juice until there are no lumps.
Then add the Ricotta cheese also softened with
pineapple juice.
If not enough pineapple juice to make up 2 cups, use water and add to mixture in the bowl.
Allow to cool in refrigerator until the mixture begins to thicken, then stir in the crushed pineapple.
Pour in a 10 x 13 x 2-inch pan or dish and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: reese's squares
directions: Mix well and spread on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put melted chocolate on top.
Eat.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl; toss lightly and chill well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: play dough(cooked)
directions: Stir dry ingredients in a heavy pan.
Mix liquids (except food coloring) and add to the dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Cook over moderate heat.
Stir until dough pulls away from the pan or until it can be formed into a ball.
Turn the dough onto a board and knead.
Add coloring and knead.
Store in an airtight container and refrigerate.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble the Oreos and place in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Mix pudding, sugar, milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over Oreos. Lightly sprinkle bits of Oreo on top of filling.
Refrigerate to set.

title: claudia hurne's brunch casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread bread cubes evenly over bottom of pan.
Mix eggs and milk. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Pour over bread cubes and let stand covered in refrigerator overnight.

title: coleslaw
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Slice cabbage into quarters and slice thinly.
Cut longer strips in half.
Chop onion and place cabbage and onion into bowl.
(I use a large Tupperware container with a lid.)

title: divinity salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk with a mixer. Stir in lemon juice, pineapple, Cool Whip and chopped nuts. Chill and serve.

title: golden beef roast
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in a browning bag or enclosed in aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for approximately 2 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into mixture of flour, salt, egg and vinegar and add water a little at a time.
Bake, with filling, at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated green bean salad
directions: Beat oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper together with a fork. Toss beans, onion rings and dressing together.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: home-canned sweet pickle sticks
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water.
Let sit for 4 to 5 hours. Pack into pint jars.
Make boiling solution (might have to triple recipe); boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over quartered cukes to within 1/2-inch of top of jar.
Put through water bath for 15 minutes. Yields approximately 18 pints.

title: baked tuna and noodles
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Add noodles and mix.
Pour in greased pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables as package directs. Drain.
Cook onion, celery and thyme in butter until tender.
Add soup and milk.
Stir until smooth.
In baking dish, combine turkey, pepper and cooked vegetables.
Add soup mixture, stirring gently to mix.
Unroll crescent rolls, pressing perforations to seal.
Cut lengthwise into 8 strips, about 3/4-inch wide.
Arrange over pie in a lattice, cutting to fit as needed.
Press ends to baking dish. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: In a small bowl, combine chicken, soy sauce and oil.
Place broccoli and 1/2 cup of broth in wok.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring once every minute. Push up sides.

title: vingina chunk pickles
directions: Make brine of salt and water; boil and pour over cucumbers, boiling hot.
Let stand one week.
In hot weather, skim daily. Drain and cut in chunks.
For the next 3 mornings, make a boiling hot solution of 1 gallon water and 1 tablespoon powdered alum and pour over the pickles; make this fresh hot bath for 3 mornings.
On the 4th morning, drain and discard alum water.
Heat vinegar, 5 cups sugar, pickling spice and celery seed to boiling point and pour over the pickles.
On the 5th morning, drain this liquid off and add 2 cups more sugar; heat again to boiling point and pour over the pickles.
On the 6th morning, drain liquid; add 1 cup sugar.
Heat and pack the pickles in jar and seal.

title: tuna cheese melts
directions: Mix tuna and mayonnaise.
Butter bread and lightly brown under broiler.
Spread tuna on toasted bread.
Add slice of tomato. Cover with slice of cheese.
Place in broiler until cheese is melted.

title: granny's hash browns
directions: Mix butter, sour cream, soup and half and half together, then add thawed hash browns.
Pour in casserole dish and top with crumbled Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Combine water and flour.
Work in cheese and sausage.
Form into walnut size balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, milk, uncooked macaroni and seasonings. Cover in 2-quart buttered casserole dish and bake.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Saute broken noodles and almonds in margarine until almost brown.
Mix together dressing ingredients.
Pour dressing over cabbage mix and onions.
Mix in noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Serve immediately.
(Noodles tend to get stiff if they sit too long.)

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beer; stir to form dough.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry coconut pie
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries, reserving liquid.
To the reserved juice, add water to make 3/4 cup.
Heat to a boil.
Add strawberry gelatin and sugar.
Stir to dissolve.
Add 1/2 cup cold water. Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg whites.

title: round or chuck steak
directions: Blend.
Marinate all day or at least 2 hours.
Fix on grill or in oven.

title: boiled custard
directions: Put milk in double boiler. Let it get warm. Add other ingredients.
Cook until it coats spoon, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bread squares
directions: Spread on toasted bread squares or crackers.
Sprinkle on additional cheese and broil.
Serve hot.

title: wieners creole
directions: Chop
onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute in cooking
oil.
When
onions
are transparent, add tomato paste and sauce.
Let simmer for 1 1/4 hours.
Add wieners.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cobblestone cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt bit by bit.
Fold in raisins.
Drop 3 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(For variety, add 1 cup coconut.)

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together eggs, condensed milk and Pet milk.
Add whipped topping.
Pour into freezer and add whole milk to fill line. Freeze until firm.

title: chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except wings, in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; turn heat down and simmer 6 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Divide wings into 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Pour sauce over the wings and bake approximately 90 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to instructions.
Mix all ingredients. Top with bread crumbs or crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexiburgers
directions: Cook your burger by your preferred method. When it's almost done to your liking, melt the cheese over the burger. Top with salsa and serve. Yield: 1 serving.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Use whole graham crackers to line bottom of a baking dish. Layer with French vanilla pudding.
Layer with Cool Whip.
Then repeat all of the layers.
On top layer use whole graham crackers. Spread with chocolate icing.
(Can be Betty Crocker or your own.)

title: fly-off-the-plate pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Combine beaten egg, milk and sour cream and add to dry ingredients, beating with slotted spoon or wire whisk.
Add cooled butter and beat until smooth.
Add a bit more milk if batter is too thick.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Bake to a golden brown on one side and turn and finish baking.
May be used for breakfast or may be topped for a main dish with chicken a la king, creamed ham, dried beef, Newburg, egg slices in sherried cream sauce, etc.

title: tomato juice
directions: Run tomatoes through Squeezo. Cook rest of ingredients together until softened. Pour into tomatoes. Simmer about 1 hour. Pour into canning jars. Seal.

title: sour cream peach ice cream
directions: In blender or food processor, puree peaches and lemon juice to measure 3 cups puree.
Pour into canister or ice cream freezer.

title: gala punch
directions: Dissolve Awake into 2 quarts water.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, add cranberry juice and ginger ale.
(Pour ginger ale along edge of punch bowl, not in the middle.) Serve with ice cubes made from orange juice with orange and lemon slices.

title: rice cream pie
directions: Mix syrup and peanut butter thoroughly.
Add Rice Krispies. Mix.
Press mixture into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill until firm.
Add the ice cream.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in a heavy pan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil over moderate heat for 9 to 10 minutes to 238° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm (110°), about 1 hour.
Add and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape. Quickly stir in walnuts and cherries.
Turn into an oiled pan. Let stand until firm before cutting.
Makes 5 1/2 pounds.

title: texan-size almond crunch cookies
directions: Combine sugar, powdered sugar, butter and vegetable oil in a large
mixing
bowl;
beat at medium speed with electric mixer until
blended.
Add
eggs
and almond extract, beating well. Combine
flours, soda, salt and cream of tartar; gradually
add to creamed mixture, beating just until blended after each
addition. Stir
in
almonds
and
brickle chips.
Chill dough 3
to
4 hours.
Shape
dough into 1 1/2-inch balls and place
at
least
3 inches
apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten cookies
with a fork dipped in sugar, making a crisscross pattern.
Bake
for
14 to 15 minutes or until lightly
browned.
Transfer to racks to cool.
Yield:
About 4 dozen.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Alternate flour mixed with salt, soda and buttermilk mixed with flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jen's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: mexican rice
directions: Mix rice, soup, sour cream, chilies, 1 cup cheese and garlic powder.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound steak.
Cut in serving pieces and dip in flour.
In a skillet, add a little oil and brown steak pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Stir often.

title: rabbit in sour cream gravy
directions: Season the marinated cut up rabbit with salt and pepper. Brown in cooking oil.
Remove the meat and set it aside.
Add the onion, celery, carrot and parsley; saute briefly.
Add flour, mustard, sugar and lemon juice to taste.
Add wine, some water, bay leaves and return the rabbit to the sauce and cook until tender.

title: tuna stuffed eggs
directions: Slice hard-cooked eggs in halves.
Remove yolks.
In small bowl, mash yolks and add remaining ingredients.
Fill reserved egg whites.
Makes 24 halves.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish. Heat in microwave.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix milk, cocoa, margarine and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir mixture as it boils for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir thoroughly and drop mixture by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: provencale stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes; discard.
Carefully scoop pulp into a bowl, leaving shells intact.
Coarsely chop pulp and set aside. Saute onion and garlic in medium nonstick skillet, coated with cooking spray.
Stir in tomato pulp, parsley, thyme, salt, pepper and basil; saute until moisture evaporates.
Remove from heat; stir in breadcrumbs.
Stuff tomato shells with breadcrumb mixture; sprinkle each with 2 teaspoons of cheese.
Place stuffed tomatoes in a small baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Yields 4 servings.
Calories: 126 (26% from fat), cholesterol 4 mg, sodium 333 mg and fat 3.7 grams.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together, then add milk and cook until desired consistency.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp. Arrange in 11 x 17-inch baking dish. Pour oil over shrimp. Combine parsley and next 3 ingredients and sprinkle over shrimp. Cover and bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Turn shrimp over and drizzle butter over shrimp. Sprinkle the bread crumbs and cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, bell pepper and celery with the salt. Soak overnight.
Drain well.
Add mustard seed, celery seed, vinegar, sugar and red pepper seeds.
Cook all together until vegetables are tender.
Have jars and lids real hot, also jars too. Makes 9 pints.
Real good with beans.

title: salad dressing rolls
directions: Measure flour into mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients. Stir.
Drop batter into greased muffin tins by tablespoonfuls. Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: very good cooked icing(an old family recipe)
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 8 minutes in iron skillet.
Take off and add 1/2 stick butter and vanilla; beat until thickens, then ice cake.

title: chili dip
directions: Press cream cheese in bottom of glass pie plate, pour chili over, then salsa, top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot with nachos or crackers.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients in small bowl; add to zucchini mixture. Add nuts. Pour into 2 ungreased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Put in microwave until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla; spread on buttered plate.

title: moist applesauce cake
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain. Put in saucepan. Add spaghetti sauce. Simmer about 10 minutes. Put macaroni in casserole dish. Add other ingredients. Mix well. Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: peas with bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Blend in flour, stir in light cream.
Add peas, cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until peas are tender, 15 minutes for fresh peas.
Add bacon, season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: all-american apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, allspice and butter with apples and lemon juice.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Dot with butter.
Place remaining pie shell on top.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine pork and beans, green pepper, onion, brown sugar, ketchup, bacon and a little bacon drippings in baking dish or pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: cashew chicken salad
directions: Use 4 large bowls.
Put in each bowl, 1/4 of first 8 ingredients.
Set aside.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of cookie dough 2-inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ranch style lentil casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Add salt to 5 cups boiling water; add lentils and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Brown beef; drain off excess oil and transfer meat to a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
To freeze, cook and seal securely.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: bubble bread
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and biscuits in plastic bag.
Shake - until biscuits are coated.
Arrange biscuits in greased tube pan.
Blend remaining cinnamon and sugar with margarine in small bowl, pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Yields 7 servings.
Approx. per serving:
cal. 503.7, prot. 7.5, total fat 19.4, chl. 44mg., car. 74.8g, sod. 1028.8mg, pot. 70.3mg.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over wings for at least 3 hours; overnight is better.
Line cookie sheet (with sides) with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat ingredients with a fork (except blueberries).
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 400°.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: ruth's depression cookies(ice box cookies)
directions: Stir first seven ingredients all together.
Pour mixture into 6 cups of flour.
Work with hands.
Add about 2 cups or so of chopped nuts, not ground too small.
Form into long narrow logs on waxed paper - wrap up and refrigerate till you want to bake.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook the chicken; take out the bones and cut into pieces. Beat the eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough broth to make it real sloppy.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: steak roquefort
directions: Sauce:
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and whip until blended and bubbling.
Do not brown.
Add wine; continue to stir while boiling for 2 minutes.
Slowly add cream; simmer 20 minutes. Add cheese and seasonings, barely returning to a boil, then remove from heat.

title: sopa del gringo
directions: In blender or food processor, combine tomatoes and their liquid, green chilies and onion.
Whirl until smooth.
Pour into a 4-quart kettle with the broth and salsa and bring to a boil.
Add turkey, rice, corn, cumin, salt, garlic and chili powder.
Heat through.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: americana casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onion and ground beef; saute until beef is thoroughly browned.
Drain off drippings.
Reserve meat mixture; set aside.
Melt remaining 1/4 cup butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add 1 cup cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add frozen vegetables and reserved meat mixture.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole; bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: portugal beans
directions: Let beans soak overnight, then cook until done.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and a little salt to beans while cooking. Cook hamburger meat and onion together until separated, not brown. Add to beans.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Let simmer one hour.
Good winter meal.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients together in a blender.
Blend until thick and creamy.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: coleslaw parfait salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Blend in mayonnaise, cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill mixture until partially set; beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds or a 1-quart mold; chill until set.

title: sweet and sour cucumber
directions: Place sliced cucumbers in bowl and mix well with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drain off all the salty fluid.
Add vinegar and sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Before serving, drain sweet and sour juice from cucumber slices and place cucumbers into a serving bowl.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Place in desired pan and cook for 1 hour or until middle is firm at 350°.

title: b l t dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together, mixing well.
Refrigerate for an hour or two before serving.
Serve with toast points or plain Melba toast.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients well,
adding
dry
ingredients gradually
stirring until batter is
moistened.
Spoon
batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch
loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 10
minutes before removing from pans.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until almost done.
Drain.
Add tuna and cream of chicken soup.
Mix together.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: summer sausage 2
directions: Day 1: Combine all ingredients, mixing well with your hands or in a food processor. Shape into 3 or 4 rolls and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: general tso's chicken(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces.
In a large bowl combine the chicken with one tablespoon regular soy sauce, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 1 tablespoon oil, beaten egg and pepper to taste. Toss well to coat chicken .
Refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.

title: hamburger mashed potato casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13 inch pan, brown hamburger and onion. Drain fat. Add green beans and soup. Mix well. Cover with mashed potatoes. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir in celery, onion, cheese, broccoli and rice.
Pour in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: zucchini, tomato and potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Thinly slice zucchini, tomatoes and potatoes.
Arrange vegetables in lightly oiled shallow casserole dish, alternating slices of vegetables.
Sprinkle with olive oil and bake until potatoes are done, around 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, salt and boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into Jell-O mold.
Chill until set.
Remove from mold and serve.
(For easier blending, whip sour cream briskly before adding to Jell-O mixture.)

title: new england family supper
directions: In Dutch oven, place smoked pork shoulder butt, seasonings and water. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add vegetables.
Continue to simmer 30 minutes. Serve meat on platter with vegetables.

title: joan's crappie chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot, except fish, butter, flour and milk.
Bring to boil.
While the other pot is coming to a boil, put butter in a nonstick skillet and saute fish until white and firm.
Add fish to boiling pot.
Use the remaining butter in skillet to make sauce.
Add flour and cream with butter over heat. Add milk, salt and pepper to taste.

title: dirty rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Fry chicken livers in 2 tablespoons oil until brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add sausage and ham pieces with 3 tablespoons water.
Cover.
Cook 5 or 6 minutes or until done.
Remove from skillet.
Chop livers into small pieces.
Mix with ham and sausage.

title: "mish-mash" hamburger stew(so easy)
directions: We enjoyed eating these when we spent summers in Arizona at the Rockpoint Mission.
First you make fry bread which the Navajos did on an open fire sometimes and then you put on the topping.

title: cheese chilies cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Whisk together eggs, yogurt and butter in a medium bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix just until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch heavy skillet and bake 40 minutes.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: Mix the buckwheat flour, all-purpose flour and salt.
Add the buttermilk and mix thoroughly to a smooth batter.
Let stand overnight.
When ready to prepare, add 1 teaspoon soda, dissolved in a little warm water to half of the batter (refrigerate remaining butter until needed).
To this half of the batter also add enough buttermilk so that batter will pour readily.
Use fat pork to grease griddle.
Set heat to 360°.
Half of the batter makes about 18 (4 to 5-inch) pancakes.
Serve only with pure maple syrup, real butter and Bob Evans sausage patties!

title: a bete gris casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking pan; line with the ground chuck or hamburger.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over top.
Spread French fries over the entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add biscuits over the top of casserole and brown for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, milk and salt. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute or until makes soft ball in water. Add vanilla. Beat until thick; pour into buttered pan.

title: grandma helen's orange delight cookies
directions: Drop cookies on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Layer all the ingredients.
Melt margarine and drizzle on top. Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not mix any of the ingredients.
Just layer each.
Note:
You can use any pie filling you choose.
Other fruits are just as good.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box mix, then mix in separate bowl the cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg.
When smooth, add to cake mixture.
Swirl cream cheese mixture in pan and bake as directed.

title: chicken dumpling pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 dish. Combine Bisquick, sour cream and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together until all ingredients are moist.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
Slice steak in thin bite-size pieces and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke; brown in oil.
Add onion and saute 3 minutes more.
Add noodles and rest of ingredients, except parsley and sour cream. Cover and cook until meat is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and parsley.
Stir to blend.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding per directions on package; set aside.
Put powdered sugar and peanut butter in bowl.
Mix until powdered sugar is coated.
Put mixture in pie shell (about 1/4-inch).
Add pudding on top.
Add rest of peanut butter mixture on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: old south brunswick stew(good cold night supper dish!)
directions: Cook meats until tender, saving the stock.
Shred meat by hand.
Mix all vegetables (except butter beans) with meats and seasonings together in a large pot; simmer on top of stove 6 to 8 hours.
Add butter beans the last hour of cooking time.
Stir frequently; if liquid is needed, add some of the meat stock. Serves 10.

title: squash preserves
directions: Peel, seed
and
cut up squash.
Boil 6 minutes.
Drain well; add
sugar,
pineapple and lemon juice.
Boil 6 minutes. Remove from
heat and add jello.
Place in sterilized jars and seal. Makes 5 pints.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over meat and bake 30 minutes or longer at 350°.
Makes enough sauce for 8 x 8-inch pan.
Double for 9 x 13-inch pan and bake one hour.

title: crab imperial
directions: Pick crab meat carefully without breaking lumps.
Cook pepper in butter for 2 minutes.
Mix all ingredients (delicately so not to break crab lumps).
Heap into 4 to 5 shells.
Top with a few bread crumbs, moistened with melted butter.
Put shells on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna and shells ala long island
directions: Cook the pasta normally and rinse in colander.
Mix the shells, tuna, celery and peas and serve hot or cold.

title: mom's skillet cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch skillet.
Remove from burner.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nutmeats over bottom.
Arrange fruit on sugar. Prepare following batter.

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Put fruit in bottom of dish and mix all other ingredients except margarine; pour over fruit using melted margarine on top. Bake in a 350° oven until crust is brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Mixture will be soft but not runny, add flour if needed.
Do not grease pan.
Generously flour hands and counter and flatten into patties. Bake approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets; skin and slice.
In pot put sugar, vinegar, water, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Cook beets in liquid until it boils again.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
No processing needed.
To seal, boil jar
lids for 10 minutes and tighten jar rings.
Let cool.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, combine next 4 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add the rest of the ingredients to mixture.
Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough into 12 x 7-inch oblong.
Spread with oleo. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up; begin at wide side. Seal well by pinching edge of dough.
Cut into 12 slices.
Place in greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan, leaving small space between each slice.
Let rise.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan. If desired, top with icing.
Makes 12.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease a large pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for eight minutes.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip; spread on first layer. Dissolve jello in water.
Mix in frozen strawberries.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour this over second layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: skillet special
directions: Heat bacon drippings in a large skillet with lid.
Put in cabbage with onions.
Add Polish sausage.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use as salad dressing on your favorite gathering of veggies.

title: glory fried chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour and brown in shortening.
Pour off grease.
Stir in soup.
Cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: In large saucepan, combine green peppers, jalapeno peppers, sugar and vinegar. Heat to boiling, boil 1 minute, then remove from heat. Stir in pectin, mixing well. Let stand 5 minutes, skim off white film which forms on top. Mix in food coloring. Strain if you prefer a clear jelly. Pour into hot sterilized jars, seal with hot lids and tighten bands. Cool on rack. Very good poured over a block of cream cheese and served with crackers.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove salmon from can, take out large bones.
Drain off liquid and save 1/4 cup.
Add flour to salmon.
Mix baking powder with liquid (this should fizz if baking powder is good).
Pour into salmon mixture.
Add egg, diced onion and pepper.
Do not add salt. Spoon out balls and drop into hot oil.
Each ball cooks in about 2 minutes.
Salmon balls will be crisp.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Prepare and cook 5 cups shredded cabbage.
Add 2 tablespoons vinegar or lemon juice to cooking salted water.
Cook bacon dices until crisp and drain.
Drain fat from skillet, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Stir sugar and flour into fat in skillet.
Stir in water, vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.
Stir until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Stir bacon and sauce mixture into hot cabbage in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with additional diced bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bread bowls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in yeast mixture and just enough buttermilk until dough leaves the sides of the bowl and forms a ball.
Knead for 1 minute or until smooth.
Cover; let rest for 10 minutes.

title: hay stacks
directions: Place chips in double boiler and melt.
Stir frequently.
When melted, stir in nuts and noodles and spoon at once onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Put caramels and 1/3 cup milk in double boiler to melt.
(Or use saucepan over low heat.)
Set aside.
Mix cake mix, margarine, nuts and remaining milk.
Press half the dough into the bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan (dough will not spread). Bake 6 to 7 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips
over dough.
Top with melted caramel mixture. Crumble remaining dough over top. Return to oven and bake 15 minutes more.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add raisins, vinegar and water.
Cook to syrup.
Serve hot.
May be reheated.

title: prime rib of beef
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place roast in open roasting pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then rub in flour.
Make a tent of aluminum foil to cover meat, just to protect the oven.
Roast for 10 minutes per pound (for rare).
When roasting time is up, turn oven off.
Leave meat in oven for 1 hour.
Do not open oven.

title: chocolate pecan crisp pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and blend well.
Melt butter and chocolate together over double boiler.
Add to egg mixture with nuts and vanilla; mix well. Pour into deep 9-inch pie shell, unbaked.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped or ice cream.
(After pie cools, it has crisp chocolate crust over the top; crust breaks apart when pie is cut).
Keep in sealed refrigerator container in the refrigerator.

title: pie crust for the freezer
directions: Cut shortening into the flour.
Add water, salt and syrup. Roll into 20 to 24 balls and store in freezer.
(I flatten the balls a little and freeze on a cookie sheet before storing.)

title: gobs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Drop from tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Make filling.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix with hands until soft.
Put in Mirro cookie press.
Use wheel with most prongs to shape.
Cut before baking.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Leave on cookie sheet until cool before removing to keep from crumbling.
Makes 200.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: Combine vinegar, catsup, sugar, Worcestershire and oil and pour over remaining ingredients. Mix and chill overnight. Serve cold.

title: crock-pot meatballs and sausage
directions: To the ground meat add bread crumbs, eggs, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper and mix well.
Shape into balls and broil in broiler until brown.
Put meatballs and sausage in a crock-pot. Mix spaghetti sauce and brown gravy mix and pour over the balls and sausage.
Cook for 3 hours on low heat in crock-pot.
Skim off any grease that comes to surface.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix soup and water together.
Remove 1/4 cup soup mixture; combine with ground beef.
Add beaten egg and mix well.
Add bread crumbs, onion, parsley and salt; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch diameter balls.
In Dutch oven, brown meat balls; drain off fat. Add remaining soup mixture, cover and cook over low heat about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add a little more water, if needed.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook thoroughly meat, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with corn bread. Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit bake
directions: Drain
all
juice.
Save pineapple juice (1 cup), brown sugar, flour
and margarine to make sauce.
Cook until thick. Put fruit in a Pyrex dish.
Pour sauce over it and refrigerate overnight. Put in oven at 350° until real bubbly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Steam one or two bunches of fresh cut broccoli.
Lay in bottom of glass casserole.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and sour cream. Stir in chicken.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Grate cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt the Hershey bars, marshmallows and water over low heat, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool.
Stir in the Cool Whip and pour into prepared crust.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix well and form into loaf. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and pour topping over loaf. Return to oven for 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup water and pour over partly thawed berries; fold in whipped cream.
Put in graham cracker crust; freeze.

title: no bake blueberry cheese pie
directions: Mix granulated sugar and cornstarch in medium size saucepan. Stir in water until blended.
Add 1 cup of the blueberries.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly until berries release their juices.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining berries.
Cool to room temperature.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Cut pork in 1/2-inch by 2-inch strips.
Brown in hot oil.
Add 1 cup water, bouillon cube and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well. Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, vanilla, eggs and butter together.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add raisins and pineapple.
Drop on cookie sheet (1/2 teaspoonful) and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in Dutch oven on top of stove until broccoli is soft and turning lighter green.
Drain in colander. Melt Velveeta on stove or microwave, stirring often.
Add soup, Worcestershire and garlic.
Stir in broccoli and onion until blended.
If too thin, let cook over low heat until thickens. Best if made day before and refrigerated.
Serve warm with snack crackers or Fritos.

title: cherry delight
directions: Line pan or square dish with graham crackers.
Prepare pudding as directed on package (using the milk).
Let set 5 minutes, then blend in Cool Whip.
Spoon half of mixture over graham crackers. Add another layer of crackers over the mixture and spoon remaining mixture over graham crackers.
Add remaining graham crackers and spoon cherry pie filling over them.
Chill before serving.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.
Can use vanilla wafers.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix together and press 3/4 of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze. Take out and press 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream on top of frozen crust.
Crumble remaining crust on top. Sprinkle 1/2 can chocolate syrup over crumbs.
Re-freeze.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes, but do not peel. Cut into 3/4-inch slices. Place on paper towel to drain. Combine flour, salt, sugar and pepper.
Dust tomatoes in flour mixture on both sides.
Add evaporated milk to remaining flour mixture to make thick batter. Dip floured tomatoes in batter. Fry in hot oil, 1/2-inch deep, until golden brown on both sides.

title: nut-cracker sweets
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
To keep the cookies from sticking, cover 2 cookie sheets with foil.
Break graham crackers on perforated lines.
Place crackers, side by side, on the foil covered cookie sheets.

title: moma gumbo
directions: The secret is in the roux.
Brown the flour in the bacon drippings until golden brown.
Add onions, tomatoes, celery, garlic and bell peppers.
Simmer and stir frequently for 15 minutes.
Place the roux in larger pot; add 3 quarts of water and half of the shrimp, crabmeat and okra.
Simmer slowly for 2 hours (the longer the better).
Then 30 minutes before serving add the remaining shrimp, crabmeat and okra.
Serve over hot rice.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut cake into 2-inch squares.
Put layer of cake, layer of pudding (while it is still thin), then Cool Whip and Butterfinger sprinkles.
Reserve some sprinkles for the very top.

title: cranberry salsa
directions: Rinse the cranberries, discarding any stems or blemished berries.
Transfer them to a medium saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Drain well and transfer to a plastic or glass container.
Add the remaining ingredients and combine with a wooden spoon.
Cover and refrigerate; use when needed.
This can be used up to 1 week.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt together chocolate bar, margarine and milk.
In bowl, beat eggs, cornstarch, sugar and vanilla.
Then add chocolate mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over top and bake at 375° for 40-50 mins.
Cool completely until set.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, flour and sugar.
Place in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and melted butter. Sprinkle on top of fruit mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Into a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, spoon peach pie filling.
Into a medium bowl, measure flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in coconut.
Crumble mixture evenly over peach pie filling.
Bake 15 minutes or until topping is golden brown and filling is bubbly.
Serve with half and half.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream together the sugars, margarine and eggs. Stir in oil and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Refrigerate until dough is firm. Form into small round balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with fork or fingertips to thin balls.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: potato salad (with eggs)
directions: Boil potatoes, cool, then peel and cut.
Add all ingredients and mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of rice and 1 pound hamburg.
Add to Swiss chard leaves.
Use toothpicks to hold leaves together.
Put 2 cans tomatoes and 1 teaspoon onion powder in large frypan or Dutch oven.
Dissolve two beef cubes in hot water; add to pan.
Place pigs in pan and bring to boil and let simmer on top of stove for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Trim any excess fat from beef.
Discard fat.
Cut beef into serving-size pieces; season with salt and black pepper to taste. Scrub potatoes.
Cut scrubbed potatoes into quarters.
Cut carrots and parsnip diagonally into 3/4 inch slices.
Slice celery into 1 1/2 to 2 inch pieces.
Place potato, carrot, parsnip, celery, onion and bay leaves in slow cooker.
Sprinkle rosemary and thyme over vegetables.
Arrange beef over vegetables in slow cooker. Pour broth over beef.
Cover slow cooker and cook pot roast on LOW about 8 1/2 to 9 hours or until beef is fork tender.
Remove beef to large serving platter.
Arrange vegetables around beef on platter.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Serve pot roast with juices from slow cooker or with gravy, if desired.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix and chill.
This salad is pretty cut and served on a lettuce leaf.
Garnish with pecan half or cherry half.

title: spicy raisin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients put in greased baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: risotto
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in rice and cook with oil.
Add wine and stir until evaporated.
Add dried mushrooms, the water they were soaked in and the tomato paste, mixed in 1/2 cup of chicken broth. Stir until liquid is absorbed.
Continue adding broth, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring constantly.
Each addition should be absorbed before adding the next.
Cook, uncovered, until broth is all absorbed and rice is tender to the bite.
Do not overcook.
Remove from stove.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir and serve.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute peppers, celery and onions down to nothing.
Add a little water at a time to keep from sticking.
Add tomatoes, sauces, beans, beef cubes and soup mix.
Cover with water and cook until cabbage is done.

title: marinated carrot and green bean salad
directions: Combine carrots, green beans and onion in glass jar with good lid.
Combine oil, vinegar, honey and salt.
Pour over vegetables. Marinate several hours or overnight (turn jar upside down a couple times).
When marinated, drain well.
(Because of the honey, you may want to blot vegetables by pouring about a third at a time on a paper towel lined platter.)
Arrange on chopped lettuce.
Garnish with pickled beets, or put marinated vegetables in glass bowl and serve as vegetable dish.

title: dole holiday treats
directions: Beat margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, orange peel and lemon peel.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; beat into margarine mixture until blended.
Stir in dates and raisins.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread slightly with back of spoon or fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Melt margarine in a sheet pan in a 300° oven.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir in brown sugar, then stir in pecans until all are coated.
Place pecans in pan with melted margarine and flatten as much as possible with a spoon.
Bake for 15 minutes, then stir and turn pecans to coat and break them up.
Stir every 15 minutes until they have cooked for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, salt lightly with Lawry's salt.
Stir again and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Bake chicken, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Remove from heat and add broth and cream.
Cook until thickened.
Add seasonings.
Cook spaghetti and combine with sauce.
Remove chicken from pan.
Spread spaghetti mixture in pan.
Put chicken on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake again for 30 minutes.

title: fire and ice tomato cocktail
directions: Chop vegetables in food processor, medium fine. Place ingredients in large mixing bowl or pitcher and cover with tomato juice.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Strain.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: In large heavy skillet, melt butter.
Add rest of ingredients in layers.
Cover and let simmer 40 minutes or until done.

title: avocado and lettuce salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce. Separate leaves and place in a bowl. Arrange thin slices of avocado over leaves. Combine rest of ingredients in a cup. Pour over salad and toss gently. Arrange on 2 salad plates and serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: low calorie macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add dressing.
Chill overnight. Next day, add vegetables,
cheese and sour cream.

title: banana yogurt
directions: In blender, combine buttermilk with banana on low speed. Gradually add ice cubes until mixture becomes thick.
Makes 1 serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in bottom of baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork, then spread over the apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and crust is brown (about 30 minutes). Top with cream or whipped cream.
You can also make this recipe using peaches.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
In shallow pan, place cornmeal, flour, sesame seed, onion salt and pepper.

title: baking powder dutch cake
directions: Mix together as pie crust and take out 3/4 cup of crumbs, then add 1 beaten egg and 1 cup milk and 2 teaspoons baking powder. Mix together and bake in pie tins.
Sprinkle crumbs over batter. Bake in greased pans 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: swedish cream
directions: Mix cream, sugar and gelatin.
Heat mixture over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and allow to completely cool at room temperature or in refrigerator.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Chill.
Beat with a whisk before serving.

title: sausage and stuffing appetizers
directions: Mix butter or margarine with water.
Stir in stuffing.
Add egg and sausage.
Blend with hands.
Chill one hour or more.
Shape into balls.
Cut bacon in thirds.
Wrap around the balls and secure with a toothpick.
Cook at 375° for 35 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: mallow topped sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except marshmallows in a lightly greased baking dish; blend well.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until sweet potatoes are hot and marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: tomato cheese snack
directions: Place tomato on bread. Put cheese on. Cut bacon in half and place on top. Put under broiler until bacon is done.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Whip butter, then add sugar and cream together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together separately the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture 1/3 to 1/2 at a time.
Mix well between each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Spray a 10-inch Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray and spoon in cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 90 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, egg and milk.
Mix and fold in berries.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger. Cool.
In skillet, mix tomatoes, garlic salt, green pepper and onions.
Cook cabbage and drain. Put in greased baking dish.
Add tomato mixture on top of cabbage. Put Swiss cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and drain.
Layer about one-half of the cabbage. Add a layer of sliced cheese.
Repeat balance of cabbage and cheese.
Dilute soup with small amount of water.
Pour over cabbage and cheese.
Cook in 350° oven until cheese is bubbly. Crumble crackers over casserole.
Return to oven and brown.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Mix cheeses and flour.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: simple pork chops
directions: Melt some Spry in a frying pan and brown chops.
Remove and use paper towel to remove any grease.
Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Mix potatoes, chops and soup in a casserole and bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
Use soup as gravy over meat and potatoes.

title: springerle(traditional anise christmas cookies)
directions: Need wooden pattern of springerle rolling pin or other mold (glass dish bottom).

title: corn salad
directions: In a medium bowl, make dressing by combining sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to blend.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pineapple chicken stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Set pineapple aside. In small bowl, combine cornstarch and juice until smooth. Stir in vinegar, catsup, brown sugar, soy sauce and ginger. Set aside. In a wok or large skillet, stir-fry chicken in 2 tablespoons oil 5 or 6 minutes. Sprinkle with garlic salt; remove and keep warm.

title: spaghetti alla puttanesca
directions: Cook the pasta in a large saucepan of boiling, salted water, following the directions on the packet.
While the water for the pasta is heating, put the olive oil in a frying pan.
Add the finely chopped garlic and chopped anchovy fillets and cook gently until they are almost melted.
Now stir in the chopped tomatoes with their juice, the black olives and capers (these can be chopped or left whole according to taste, but if the olives are large it is better to chop them).
Cook for 5 minutes.
When the pasta is ready, drain it and add the sauce.
Mix well; sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve immediately.

title: white potato pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or food processor until thoroughly mixed. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, until set. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix Dream Whip, milk and vanilla until fluffy.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pat graham cracker crumbs in pan.
Pour in mixture. Top with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: fudge
directions: Butter saucepan and combine ingredients, stirring constantly until fudge is soft ball stage.
Add butter and let set until the bottom of the pan is warm.
Add vanilla and beat until fudge loses its gloss.
Add chopped pecans and pour into buttered pan.

title: cherry oat cookies
directions: Oven at 350°.
Sprinkle cherries with rum.
Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in egg and zest.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into butter mixture.
Stir in oats and cherries.
Place spoonfuls of dough 1 1/2-inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from sheets.

title: grandma ann's date bars
directions: Cream egg and sugar.
Add milk.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add dates and pecans.
Then add to creamed mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for about 20 minutes or until edges are lightly browned and center springs back.
Cool in pan and cut into bars about 1 x 3-inch.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Blend well.
Add flour, cocoa, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon and salt.
Stir together.
Add zucchini; mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Does not require frosting!
Bake in glass pan at 325° for 45 minutes; metal pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients (except soda) together.
Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add soda to persimmon pulp.
Mix together.
When completely mixed, fold in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and stem mushrooms.
Add onions and bacon to softened cream cheese.
Mix well.
Fill mushroom caps with cheese mixture. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Can be browned under boiler, if you wish.

title: chicken cortez
directions: Cook chicken breasts in glass dish covered with waxed paper for 16 to 18 minutes.
Cool; tear into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, sour cream, evaporated milk, soup, hot sauce, onion, celery, chilies, tortillas and cheeses; blend well.
Microwave for 12 to 14 minutes, turning halfway through cooking time.

title: grandma's sausage turkey stuffing(for 15 pound turkey)
directions: Grind all ingredients (uncooked) together.
Mix well.
Stuff into turkey just prior to baking.
Bake according to turkey directions.

title: creole shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl except mayonnaise.
Toss with the mayonnaise dressing just before serving.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add melted margarine.
Add coconut and nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until firm.
Makes 3 if in bought frozen crusts or two 9-inch crusts of your own.
May freeze after baked and cold.

title: diabetic banana nut cake
directions: Mash bananas.
Combine oil, Sucaryl, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix.
Add bananas.
Add flour slowly.
Add raisins and nuts last. Will be stiff.
Pour into 2 deep pans about 3 x 5-inch depth. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise and place in bottom of 9 to 10-inch clear pie plate.
Layer in order on top of cream cheese mixture:
cocktail sauce, shredded cheese and chopped shrimp.
Combine and layer on top of shrimp:
green pepper and scallions.
Refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator one hour before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch glass dish with melted margarine.
Mix in all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes or until brown on sides.

title: low-fat pie
directions: Put everything except Cool Whip and graham cracker crumbs in blender and blend until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs in bottom of pie plate.
Pour mixture over crumbs; refrigerate.

title: potato bread
directions: Mix together mashed potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in milk and add to cooled potato mixture. Add eggs to this mixture.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Cover dough with a cloth and set in a warm place to double in bulk. Knead down dough and make into loaves, hot rolls, cinnamon rolls, coffee cake or spudnuts.
Let rise until doubled in size again. Bake in 350° oven, except for spudnuts which are deep fried.
Bake loaves 1 hour approximately.
Hot rolls about 12 minutes. Cinnamon rolls about 15 minutes.
Coffee cake about 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: grease bottom only of 9x13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix pecans and coconut and spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and spoon over cake batter. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
During baking, it cracks on the top resembling the aftermath of an earthquake.

title: pretty pink
directions: Mix cheese with Cool Whip.
Stir in jello (dry).
Mix well and add pineapple.
Refrigerate for a short time.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Roll into balls and bake on cookie sheet in center of oven at 325°, turning as they brown. Bake about 15 to 20 minutes on each side.
Makes approximately 25 balls.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together 1 cup the sugar, flour and melted butter.
Beat egg yolks until light and add to mixture (save egg whites for meringue).
Slowly add milk and salt.
Pour into large bowl; cook in microwave until thick (stir mixture once or twice).
Pour into 9-inch cooked pie crust.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until well blended.
Add other ingredients (except pecans) and mix well. Chill. After chilled, shape in a ball and roll in pecans.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk, Old Bay, Tabasco sauce, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken breasts and allow to marinate for 3 to 4 hours.
Pour flour onto large plate.
Remove chicken breasts from marinade and coat with flour.
Place floured chicken on wax paper and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Remove chicken from refrigerator and allow to warm to room temperature (about 15 minutes).
In a large frying pan or skillet, heat oil to 370°.
Cook chicken breasts one at a time for about 7 to 10 minutes each side until brown and cooked through.
Drain chicken breasts on paper towels.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Pour milk into large mixing bowl.
Add pie filling.
Mix in instant coffee.
Beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Remove from freezer; let stand 10 minutes to soften.
Top with fudge sauce.
Store any leftover in freezer.

title: summer alarm clock
directions: This was usually put into a pottery gallon jug, the kind molasses was always kept in in the winter.
Today a thermos would be used.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach according to directions; drain most of the juice (but don't press out excess juice).
Add all the ingredients, putting eggs in last.
Pour into a well buttered casserole or souffle dish.
Spread the surface with buttered bread cubes (white or French bread).
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in the middle of oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snicker bars cake
directions: Stir together dry
ingredients.
Mix
together
all the cake ingredients except for
the
Snicker bars in large mixing bowl. Mix for 30 seconds
on low speed, then for 3 minutes on high. Stir in Snicker
bars.
Grease
and
flour 8-inch round cake pans. Pour batter into
pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham breakfast casserole
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Mix the remainder and pour over.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes foil covered; remove foil for the last 10 minutes.
This is great to make in advance for breakfast or lunch guests.
Also keeps well in oven, warmed.

title: watergate salad
directions: Dissolve the pudding in pineapple juice.
Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: mexican taco casserole
directions: Combine and put in large casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: very moist cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar well.
Add nuts, coconut, pineapple, flour and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a tube pan on lower rack in oven.
When baked, punch holes in top of cake and pour the glaze over cake.
Leave in pan overnight.

title: cornish meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute first four ingredients and add next 6 ingredients.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix with beef mixture and stir in sour cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients; add oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes or until light brown at 350°.
(I roll the dough in small balls.)
Add raisins if you like.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in 7 1/2 x 10-inch greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips or corn flakes or Pepperidge Farm dressing or a combination of any of these.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into
very thin strips. In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook 1/2 the beef and 1/2 the onion until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender. Set aside.
Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.

title: homemade perogies
directions: Cook potatoes and mash with cream cheese, cheese whiz and salt. Take the 1/2 of noodle, place one tablespoon of potato filling on noodle.
Roll up and place in cake pan.
Do this with remaining noodles and potato filling.
Saute onions in oleo, pour over top of perogies.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
(Makes 2 pans.)

title: baked zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and trim ends; slice into 1/2-inch slices. Slice onion and quarter.
Melt butter; place in a shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Layer zucchini, onion and corn.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil a large fryer and debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Fry large onion in margarine.
Cool slightly.
Add cream of chicken soup, water and diced chicken.
Heat and stir into drained spaghetti.
Stir in Cheddar cheese until lightly mixed. May also add bell pepper if you like.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Whisk mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: quick brunswick stew
directions: Cook okra according to package directions.
Add onion.
Don't drain, reserve.

title: doretta's chili
directions: In large pot, cook ground meat over medium heat, breaking up with fork until loses pink color. Pour off fat. Return to heat. Add chopped onion and continue to saute until onion turns soft and clear. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Mix these ingredients with meat and onion. Add 3 cups hot water. Return to heat. Stir until begins to simmer. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Add Ranch Style beans and Wolfe brand chili and simmer 10 more minutes. Taste and adjust seasonings. Serve over rice.

title: cherry pie crunch
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch pan while heating oven to 350°. Coat pan and pour out excess butter to use later.
Put cherry pie filling in pan.
Mix cake mix and nuts together and put on top of filling.
Pour butter on top.
Bake about 40 minutes.

title: watergate cake
