directions: Mix in order and bake in 3 layers or 9 x 12-inch pan at 325°.

title: fat-free potato wedges(serves 4)
directions: Wash well and cut unpeeled potatoes into wedges.
Combine remaining ingredients in a plastic Ziploc bag.
Add potato wedges into bag and shake to coat with powdered mixture.
Leave 1-inch unzipped midway on Ziploc bag.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water in heavy pan until it will spin a thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook from 5 to 10 minutes.
When it begins to change color, add butter, then soda.
Stir well.
Pour out on a flexible buttered pan and spread as thin as possible.
Let cool. Will break into small chips.

title: ghoul-ade (black punch)(great for halloween parties)
directions: Dissolve both packages Kool-Aid and sugar in 3 quarts ice water in nonmetal pitcher.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Mix together and simmer at least 20 minutes.
Strain before serving.
Garnish with thin orange slices if desired.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: cream pie with graham cracker crust
directions: Mix and form in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Cook flour and milk together; cool.
Beat Crisco and add sugar. Add flour and milk mixture to Crisco and sugar mixture and beat until fluffy.

title: hot artichoke crab spread
directions: Saute green onions, garlic and butter over medium heat, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until fairly creamy over low heat.
Serve in a chafing dish or something to keep warm during serving.
I serve with Carr's cracked pepper water crackers.

title: crispy potato wedges(low calorie)
directions: In a reusable plastic bag.
Combine the first 4 ingredients. Spritz the potato wedges with butter flavored spray.
Place in the bag a few at a time, and shake to coat.
Arrange in a single layer on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450 for 25-30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 2 Servings - 1 Point Each.

title: apricot brandy slushy
directions: Put tea bags in 2 cups of water and bring to a boil and brew for 3 minutes.
After you add sugar, squeeze tea bags and add all ingredients.
Freeze.
Once this starts to freeze, stir to keep liquor distributed; sugar will dissolve.
Put in big tub or ice cream container.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
in
large bowl.	Pour in Bundt cake pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.	Easy and good! Time of preparation: 10 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: jose's dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add the taco seasoning as package directs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat while stirring until blended and warm.
Serve as dip with chips, veggies, etc. (Works well in crock-pot.)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Put brown sugar over top, sprinkle coconut, pecans and marshmallows.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Heat barbecue sauce and apple jelly until jelly is dissolved. Put wings in sauce and leave overnight.
Bake in slow oven at 300° to 325° for about 2 1/2 hours.
Wings should be tender, but not falling apart.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Combine oil and flour in a large Dutch oven; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is the color you prefer, dark.
Stir in celery, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Brown okra in small saucepan and add to pot.
Stir well over low heat for a few minutes.
You may cool and freeze mixture for later use at this stage.
Add the next 9 ingredients; simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Fifteen minutes before serving, add shrimp and crabmeat, chicken and oysters (if desired).
Stir in brown sugar; simmer and serve over rice.
Recipe may be halved without loss of flavor or taste.
Yields about 7 quarts.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter Crisco and eggs and mix.
Add water and vanilla; mix.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon and mix well.
Put 1 large teaspoon dough on cookie sheet. Impress a hollow.
Put in one teaspoon of Raisin filling or Pineapple Filling, then put another dab of dough on top.

title: watergate salad
directions: Make the pudding according to package instructions.
Fold in the Cool Whip and then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: salsa
directions: Cut tomatoes, onions and peppers into what size you want for chunkiness. Mix all together and boil for 15 minutes. You then need to do a tomato bath (like canning tomatoes) and boil with lids for another 30 minutes. This makes 12 pints.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Must use Pillsbury sugar cookie dough.

title: all fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl toss sugar together with fruit.
Put butter in an 8 x 10-inch ovenproof serving dish and place in oven to melt.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into a bowl.
Stir in milk to make a batter.
Pull hot dish of melted butter from oven and pour in bottom which will bubble around sides.
Quickly spoon fruit and juice evenly over batter.
Return to oven and bake until done and rises up around the fruit.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: whole wheat yeast biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Mix well, then knead well.
Place in greased bowl; put in refrigerator about 30 minutes.
Take out and roll on floured board or paper.
Cut into biscuits; place in greased pans. Let rise at room temperature or warm place until puffed.
Bake at 375° to 400°.
Leftovers may be frozen and reheated as needed. This makes about 36 average size biscuits.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump apple pie filling in pan.
Dump crushed pineapple with juice over apples.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Melt butter; blend in sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan until top springs back when touched (40 to 45 minutes).

title: applesauce casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mixed pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat well.
Place 2/3 of the wafer crumbs in an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Pour all mixed ingredients (except cracker crumbs) into dish.
Top with remaining crumbs. Chill.

title: coffee ring
directions: Place nuts in the bottom of a greased pan.
Place rolls on the top of this.
Pour the dry pudding on top and sprinkle brown sugar over the entire mixture.
Set in a warm place and let rise to the top of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
You can mix and freeze in pan until ready, then put it on the cabinet and let it rise overnight.
It will be ready to cook in the morning.

title: peaches 'n cream crisp
directions: Drain canned peaches.
If fresh peaches are used, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Arrange peach slices in a greased 8 inch square or round pan.
Combine oats, sugar, flour and butter. Spread over peaches.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Six servings.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter, shortening, peanut butter, sugar and eggs. Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls; press
with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandma's frosting(german)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread on a warm white cake (8 x 8-inches).
Broil until frosting browns.
Be careful, it burns very quickly.
Double recipe for 8 x 11-inch or larger cake.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: Parboil chicken; let cool for 20 minutes.
While boiling chicken, chop all vegetables into strips, except carrots.
Put vegetable oil in pan (saute).
Heat oil; put in peppers and onions until onions are opaque.
Add in order:
zucchini (cook until opaque), mushrooms and tomatoes; turn down.
Take carrot and peel after cleaned; put peels into stir-fry.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces; add to stir-fry.
Next add poultry seasoning, salt and pepper to taste, Italian seasoning, garlic powder and a pinch of ginger.
After all ingredients are in the stir-fry, cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until everything is heated evenly.
Serve plain or over noodles or rice.
Serves 4 people.

title: cocoa gravy and biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add a small amount of the milk to make a paste.
Add rest of milk and cook on medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot, buttered biscuits.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar by melting it in a heavy saucepan until it becomes a golden brown syrup.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
In a second saucepan, stir together the remaining sugar, cream and butter.
Warm cream mixture over low heat.
Pour caramelized sugar into cream mixture and cook to the soft ball stage (240°).
Cool to 140°.
Beat to spreading consistency and spread on a cooled cake.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine Sugar, Cornstarch and Salt. Stir in Milk and Water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Turn to low heat and add small amounts of cooked mixture to the Eggs. Mix well and return Egg mixture to saucepan and continue stirring. Mix in 1-3/4 cups of the Chocolate Morsels and stir until melted. Allow mixture to come to a boil and thicken on low for 3 minutes (continually stirring). Remove from heat and add Vanilla and Peanut Butter; stir until melted.

title: chicken and hash brown bake
directions: Thaw hash browns overnight in refrigerator.
Layer in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chicken and mushrooms over potatoes.
Mix sour cream, broth, soup, onion and red pepper.
Pour over all. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts, 4 squares grated white baking chocolate and 1 egg; mix well.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all of above ingredients.
Form into a roll then roll in chili powder mix enough to coat outside.
Wrap and refrigerate. Slice when ready to use.
Keeps well frozen.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Sift flour 3 times and measure.
Add spices, nuts and raisins. Mix together and set aside.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten egg yolks, then buttermilk with soda mixed in it, then jelly, then add flour mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in large angel food cake pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together in a small bowl and set aside.

title: curried cauliflower and potato soup(makes 5 cups)
directions: Combine the leek, oil and water in a large broad saucepan. Cover and sweat the leek over very low heat until tender, about 10 minutes.
Do not allow to brown.
Stir in the curry, ginger and turmeric.
Saute, stirring for about 1 minute.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put in greased casserole one layer chicken, one layer celery and one layer cracker crumbs.
Repeat chicken and celery.
Pour soup, diluted with milk over casserole and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend sugar, brown sugar, shortening and add 2 eggs. Beat until fluffy. Add flour mixture. Add oats, vanilla and chocolate chips. Bake 10 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheet.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, cutting in butter.
Place half of the mixture in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add whole cranberry sauce with lemon juice.
Add other half of crunch mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together	shortening,
sugars,
vanilla and eggs. Sift flour, soda and
salt.
Stir into creamed mixture;	blend well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon two inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake
at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet
about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Yields
6 to 8 dozen cookies, according to size.

title: chocolate fudge ii
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla; cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Set aside and let cool.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy and thick.
Pour in greased pan.
When cold, cut in squares.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugar and mix until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add to other mixture alternately with milk to which vanilla has been added.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: marie's supper
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Soak potatoes in hot water.
Grate as you would for hash browns.
Grate carrots, dice onions.
Mix together soup and water in electric skillet or crock-pot.
Layer hamburger meat then potatoes then carrots, then onions.
Pour soup mixture over top of meat.
Cover and cook at 250° in skillet, 8 hours in crock-pot.
Just before serving top with cheese.
Use low setting on crock-pot.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Beat egg yolks and add milk and butter.
Beat into flour mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour 3 tablespoons butter onto hot griddle for each cake and bake until top is bubbly and edges look cooked.
Turn and cook until remaining side is brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Combine 1 stick melted butter and 1 tube of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together, mix and set aside 1/4 of the mixture.
Line a medium-sized casserole with remaining mixture. Add your favorite filling recipe, then put the rest of the hamburger mixture over the top of the filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until hamburger is finished.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut up nuts, dates and orange slices into small pieces; add coconut.
Melt butter and pour over the mixture.
In another bowl, mix eggs, sugar, flour, soda and milk.
Pour over nut mixture and mix well.
Bake in a 300° oven.

title: apple squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seed.
Lay squash halves in baking dish.
Fill dish with 1/2 inch water.
Sprinkle inside of squash with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cut apples into pieces 1 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch.
Fill opening in squash with pieces of apple, raisins, pieces of walnut (fill to almost overflowing).
Put a pat of butter on top and sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and ground cloves.
Bake, covered, at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: pastel dessert or salad
directions: Combine pudding mix, jello and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil and is thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare whipped topping according to directions on package.
Thoroughly blend this into chilled mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fiesta pinwheels
directions: In medium bowl combine Fiesta dip and sour cream together. Spread on flour tortillas, roll up and cut into pinwheels.
Store in refrigerator.

title: goodbye turkey casserole
directions: Sift flour, 2 teaspoons salt and onion salt into butter.
Stir in milk slowly.
Cook over hot water until thickened.
Pour Minute rice into a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Combine broth and remaining salt and pour over rice.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over rice. Top with asparagus, then turkey.
Pour milk sauce over top. Sprinkle remaining cheese, then almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Feeds 24 persons!

title: noodle frank dinner
directions: Heat cheese in large saucepan over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
May use 1/2 cup cubed ham for frankfurters.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Beat the egg and add milk and salmon; sift the dry ingredients twice.
Add lemon juice.
Drop by spoon into deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Coat the chicken breasts with flour.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Brown chicken on both sides. Add soup and 1/2 can of water.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: polly's ranger cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add oats, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin torte cheesecake
directions: For crust, mix graham crackers, 1/3 cup sugar and oleo.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Mix with 1 1/2 cups sugar and cream cheese.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool completely.
While crust is baking, put in large saucepan the pumpkin, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup milk, salt, cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice.
Cook together for 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Remove from heat and add Knox gelatine that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Mix well.
Cool completely.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Fold into cooled pumpkin mixture and spread over cheesecake.
Spread 1 (12 ounce) Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: granny's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with fork.
Add cup of milk and blend until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead lightly and roll 3/4-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits.
Place on lightly buttered pan and brush tops of biscuits with butter.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugars and oleo or butter. Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls about the size of small walnuts.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies. Decorate with colored sugars, candy or nuts before baking.

title: royal drug store chile
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on low heat for 3 hours. Very good to freeze.

title: phyllis' red velvet cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar, beating thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well (use your mixer).
Alternately add flour and buttermilk. Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to first mixture.
Add salt, vanilla and soda.
Beat well.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes in 3 (8-inch) cake pans or square 9 x 13-inch pan.
Grease and flour pan.
Cool and then frost.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large oven bag.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add spaghetti sauce to bag. Squeeze bag to blend.
Add chicken and green pepper; turn bag to coat chicken.
Arrange chicken in an even layer.
Close bag with tie.
Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes. Serve over hot pasta.

title: wisconsin cheese `n' beer soup
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and cook flour over medium heat, stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until bubbling. Stir in golden onion soup mix thoroughly blended with milk and Worcestershire sauce. Bring just to boiling point, then simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish, if desired, with additional cheese or parsley. Makes about 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Thaw spinach souffle and then stuff the mushroom caps. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baby ruth candy
directions: Mix sugar and white syrup.
Bring just to a boil (do not let boil).
Add crunchy peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered pan.
Melt chocolate pieces and butterscotch and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes, then slice.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Fry ground beef, onion and celery.
Add tomatoes, water, beans, salt and pepper.
Bring to hard boil.
Add cabbage.
Turn to low heat and cook until done.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Preheat oven
to
Brown
ribs
on
top of stove. Remove from pan.
Saute
bacon
and
onions
in same pan.
Add juice, soy sauce and brown sugar; heat.
Add remaining ingredients,
then stir
in
cornstarch.
Cook until thickened and becomes transparent
(after bubbling begins, approximately 10 minutes). Pour sauce over ribs and bake in 325° oven one hour or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
In a large skillet, saute onion and margarine. Add cheese and soup to onion mixture.
Stir until cheese melts. Add broccoli (thaw broccoli in microwave for 7 minutes).
Add rice.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter roll
directions: Roll out each biscuit until thin.
Put 4 thin slices butter and 3 teaspoons sugar in center of each.
Fold and crimp edges as in fried pies.
Place in baking dish.
Combine milk and vanilla and pour over biscuit wedges.
Bake in 325° oven about 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to box.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding until gone.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until done.
Remove chicken and dice. Add soup mix and noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Add chicken and remove from heat.

title: irresistible cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour, oatmeal and soda; mix well.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and raisins; stir until well mixed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, stir together all dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Cut into bars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Add egg, sour cream, corn bread and corn.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: tuffies(cookies)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts, dates and coconut and mix well.
Pour and spread into floured and greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or can be layered (the texture is stiff, so you may have to press it down with a large spoon).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares and roll each square in powdered sugar.

title: jalapeno-pimento squares
directions: Combine all; stir well.
Spread mixture in lightly greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: luau ribs
directions: Boil ribs for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Broil ribs over slow coals or gas grill (low) about 10 minutes.
Brush with sauce.
Broil about 20 minutes, brushing frequently with sauce and turning often.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken breasts with mushrooms
directions: Pound chicken to tenderize.
Marinate for 1 hour in well beaten eggs.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in butter until golden brown.
Place in a 9x
13-inch pan in one layer.
Add a layer of mushrooms and a layer of cheese.
Pour chicken broth over everything.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes marinating with broth.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.	Spray Pam nonstick cooking spray in bottom of pan.
Pour half of chips in pan.
Layer with meat and cheese until gone.
Put rest of chips on top and bake until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with your favorite salad.

title: anisette cookies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar slowly, while still beating, until thick and "lemon-colored."
Add oil and anise extract and beat 30 seconds on high speed.
Lower speed and gradually add flour, one cup at a time.
Add baking powder after first cup of flour.

title: fresh tomato and basil quiche
directions: Unroll dough, separate into strips.
Coil 1 strip around itself in a spiral.
Add second strip to end of first strip, pinching ends to seal.
Repeat until you have an 8-inch flat circle.
Roll dough into 13-inch circle; fit into 9-inch quiche dish, coated with spray.
Fold edge under, put aside.
Spray nonstick skillet with oil; add oil, place on medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute 8 minutes until lightly browned.
Spread onion mix over crust; sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange tomato slices over cheese; top with basil.
Combine milk and next 4 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour over tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted 1 inch from center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Fat 6.9 grams.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup of milk. Set aside.
Mix dry cake mix, pecans, 1/3 cup milk and margarine.
Pat 1/2 cake mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Pour caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts and syrup in casserole dish.
Cook on High 4 minutes; stir.
Cook 3 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Add soda; stir and pour on greased cookie sheet (quickly).

title: philly cream cheese brunch quiche
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 12-inch circle. Place in 10-inch pie plate.
Turn under edge; flute.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until pastry is lightly browned.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Chill the can of cherry pie filling, pineapple, and Eagle Brand milk overnight in their cans.
The next day, drain pineapple; mix in a large bowl with other ingredients. Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Thoroughly crush Oreo cookies in large bowl (a blender can be used).
Mix together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar in another bowl.
In another bowl mix pudding and milk.
Combine cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In 8-inch plastic flowerpot, use the Cool Whip lid to cover the hole in bottom of the planter.
Layer crumbs and pudding mixture beginning and ending with cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight to set. Garnish with gummy worms and an artificial flower.
Serve with a garden trowel.

title: collector's cocoa cake
directions: Beat 1 minute at medium speed. Bake at 350° until done.

title: salmon with potato "scales"
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a little oil or butter until soft. Add mushrooms and cook until most of the mushroom liquid has evaporated.
Add wine mixture and reduce by half.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: best fruit cake
directions: Empty cake mix into bowl.
Add applesauce, eggs and salt. Beat 3 minutes until creamy.
Combine fruit and nuts with flour and mix well.
Stir into the batter.
Bake in slow oven at 275° about 2 hours.
Cool thoroughly.
Wrap tightly in moisture proof wrap.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes three 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch cakes or five 3 x 5 1/2-inch cakes.
When using small pans, bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 275°.

title: chinese roast chicken
directions: Combine onion, celery, apples, raisins and walnuts.
Mix well and stuff inside of chicken.
Baste chicken with soy sauce and then honey.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Baste about every 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti primavera with chicken
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Cut chicken into 1 inch cubes.
Cut the mushrooms into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Cut the bell pepper into slivers.
Coarsely chop the scallions.
Add the spaghetti to the water and cook until al dente, 10 to 12 minutes. In a large skillet, warm 2 tablespoons of oil over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken and saute until chicken turns white, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the mushrooms, bell pepper, scallions, garlic and remaining 3 tablespoons oil.
Saute the vegetables until softened and brown, 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain spaghetti and add to the skillet with dill, salt and pepper.
Toss and serve.

title: harry chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts so meat is equal thickness.
Mix honey, soy sauce, garlic powder and pepper in a mixing cup.
Put chicken breasts in container and pour honey, etc. over chicken breasts. Put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Cook over charcoal 3 minutes per side.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions and add 1 1/2 cups pecan pieces to mix.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour in mix.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered container.
Refrigerate for 7 to 8 hours to marinate.
(If wings are frozen, thaw in marinade.
Keep turning over to be sure all wings are marinated.) Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If not brown enough, place under broiler for a few minutes.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Season pork chops well on both sides with salt and pepper. Brown in skillet, using as little oil as possible.
Remove chops. Drain fat but leave 1 tablespoon fat.
Slice in onions and brown lightly in the fat.
Add hot water and soup, diced celery, chopped green pepper, parsley and raw rice.
Add a little more salt and pepper and bay leaf, if desired.
Mix well.
Pour over browned chops in a casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° or until the meat and rice are tender.
Add additional hot water, if needed.
Serves 6.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Combine flour, Accent, salt, pepper and paprika.
Sprinkle over chicken pieces. Dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and continue baking 20 minutes longer.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until slightly crisp. Drain and cool. Add onion and green pepper slices.

title: skillet pasta roma
directions: In
large skillet brown sausage.
Add onion and garlic. Cook until
onion
is
soft; drain.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce,
water
and
pasta.
Cover
and
bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in mushrooms; simmer 5 minutes. Serve
in skillet garnished with cheese and parsley. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese, salt, pepper and butter together; stir. Put in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix these ingredients in a large bowl.
Use electric mixer. Bake in 3 layers or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and salt.
Add yeast and milk.
Add flour until it forms a soft dough. Knead on floured board a few minutes.
Put in large, oiled bowl and cover with cloth.
Let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cut in desired shape.
Put in pan and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake in 425° oven.
Makes 50 rolls.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix, roll thin and bake.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to jello.
Dissolve jello.
Add cherry pie filling and drained pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and sour cream.
Fold in nuts.
Spread on top of salad when it is completely congealed.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Will fill a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Melt sugar and butter together over low heat (stir while melting).
Add nuts and flour mixture while hot, then beaten egg yolks.
The batter will be crumbly.
Mix scraping as it tends to stick.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
The egg whites make it thin enough to pour.
Pour into greased and floured large sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut in squares while hot and sprinkle or roll in confectioners sugar.
Serves 32.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Pound and lightly flour chicken tenderloins.
Saute in butter. In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add white wine, Dijon mustard and heavy cream.
Mix with whip or whisk.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until sauce thickens.
Place chicken over rice, noodles or pasta.
Cover with Dijon sauce.
Garnish with parsley flakes.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Reserve 1/4
drippings. Crumble bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons.
Microwave beans as directed and drain.
Add mushrooms and onions to reserved 1/4 bacon drippings. Cook on medium heat 10 minutes.
Drain. Add bacon, hot green beans and pepper.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 2-quart serving dish.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Add chopped celery, onions, carrots and olives to taste.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: self-crust peach pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie shell with sliced peaches.
Cream together sugar with margarine.
Add flour, egg and vanilla.
Spread this mixture over the sliced fruit and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is golden and brown.

title: jahan's favorite parmesan chicken
directions: Mix lemon juice and eggs together.
Mix Parmesan cheese and breadcrumbs together.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture and then into bread crumbs.
Put chicken on cookie sheet.
Pour melted butter over chicken and bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, cheeses and salt and pepper in ovenproof casserole dish or pan.
Heat milk and butter until melted.
Add to potato and cheese mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients together. Make a well in the dry ingredients, then add liquid all at once. Beat thoroughly. our into greased 8 inch square pan. Bake at 400 degrees 25-30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: american lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Put softened cream cheese and butter in a large mixing bowl. Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in powdered sugar gradually and mix well.
Melt chocolate in 1/4 cup water in top of double boiler and stir into sugar mixture. Divide this into half.
Reserve one half for frosting.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Combine all ingredients except tuna and simmer until heated through; add tuna and heat thoroughly.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: sausage meat balls
directions: Combine sausage, eggs, bread crumbs and sage; form into small balls.
Brown; pour off fat.
Mix ketchup, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Pour over meat balls.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies through food processor.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar together.
Blend in 2 packages of pudding, milk and the Cool Whip.
Mix about 5 minutes.
Layer (a sand pail for kids or a flowerpot for adults) with the crumbs and cream mixture and end with the crumbs.
Add a shovel and there you have it.
Kids love this dessert.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line buttered dish with tortillas.
Layer chicken, onions and green pepper.
In medium bowl, mix soups with chili powder until red.
Pour into casserole (over chicken mixture).
Cover with cheese and dribble tomato sauce for color.
Bake covered for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Uncover for 5 minutes until cheese melts and browns a little.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter a large baking sheet before you start.
Keep it handy.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend 1/2 cup of butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl. Add eggs; using a wooden spoon, beat well.
Combine flour, 1/3 cup of cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend into egg mixture and stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from pan sides.
Cool.

title: cottage cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in pineapple syrup over low heat; add gelatin softened in cold water.
Chill until partially set; add pineapple and cheese.
Fold in whipped cream and chill until firm.

title: rice with beef broth and mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or 15 minutes in microwave.

title: tuna tempter
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until crisp-tender, but not brown. Blend in soup and milk. Add tuna and pimento.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, cook beef, sausage and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients except the noodles and cheeses.
Simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish, layer a third of the noodles and meat sauce, half of the cottage cheese, a third of the mozzarella and a third of the parmesan.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, meat sauce, mozzarella and parmesan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; uncover and bake for 20 minutes.
Let stand for 20 minutes before cutting.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: peg's chicken mornay
directions: Peel potatoes and slice in half lengthwise.
Place in a greased oblong pan flat side down.	Place chicken on top of potatoes.
Pour undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours covered at 325°, then uncover; sprinkle cheese over top and bake for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Mix flour, 1 1/3 cups sugar, 4 tablespoons cocoa and milk. Add shortening and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and pour into greased loaf pan.

title: meat loaf for one
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In a small bowl, beat egg, milk, 1 tablespoon catsup, Worcestershire, mustard, garlic powder, salt, pepper and celery seed with fork.
Beat in bread, then add meat. Mix thoroughly to a pasty mixture.
In a small baking dish, form mixture into a loaf about 3 x 6 inches.
Spread remaining catsup over loaf and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf, 6 to 8 slices.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until serving time.
Allow pie to thaw slighlty (just enough for slicing) before serving.

title: banana icebox pie
directions: Blend the milk and lemon juice in a bowl, then fold in bananas.
Pour into the pastry shell.
Chill.
Cover with whipped cream just before serving.

title: golden turkey or chicken bake
directions: Combine crumbs with melted margarine; set aside for topping. Stir together remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli-bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small skillet, heat 1 teaspoon margarine until bubbly.
Add onion and garlic and saute until onion is softened.

title: reuben dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to a small ovenproof casserole and bake, covered, for 30 minutes or until bubbles form around edges.
Remove cover and bake for 5 minutes more.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Slice the vegetables into long 1/4-inch thick slices.
Toss in the olive oil and season well with the Southwest Seasoning on both sides. Place on a hot grill and watch carefully, they can burn quickly.

title: whole wheat pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flours and cheese in large mixing bowl.
Add yeast mix; beat at low until well blended.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth (5 minutes).
Cut dough into 32 pieces.
Shape each into ball.
Roll each ball into a 14-inch rope.
Twist each into pretzel shape.
Place on baking sheets with cooking spray.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone it. Save 1 cup of broth.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel. In casserole dish, layer 1/2 bag crushed chips, 1/2 soup mixture, chicken, cheese and another layer of chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tremendous
directions: Mix together rice and soup; put in bottom of greased casserole.
Put chicken pieces on top.
Chicken breasts or thighs are best.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Pour over all this a mixture of 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 1/2 cans water.
Cover; bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours longer.
This may also be cooked at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine.
Put in 9 x 13-inch oblong greased pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: my favorite brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ann lander's meatloaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 or 3 strips of bacon.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and blueberries; reserve the juice.
Heat the reserved juices and 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Pour this liquid over the Jell-O and stir to mix thoroughly.
To this, add the pineapple and blueberries.
Stir all together well; chill for several hours until set.

title: artificial nuts(for people who cannot eat nuts)
directions: In a heavy pan, melt oleo.
Add oatmeal, stir well.
Add flour, blend again.
Add brown sugar, mix and blend thoroughly again.
Use anywhere you would use nuts.
Delicious on ice cream. Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Store in tight container in refrigerator.

title: dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread
into
small
loaf pan (6 x 10-inch).
Add one can
of chili (no beans).
Spread on salsa. Add grated cheese on top.
Bake
until	cheese melts or pop in microwave until melted.
Eat with Mexican style chips.

title: party potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes in a large casserole.
Mix 1/4 cup margarine and corn flakes and sprinkle on the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Will serve 16.

title: nacho chicken
directions: Grease bottom of casserole pan.
Crush enough tortilla chips to cover bottom of casserole.
Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of shredded cheese.
Pour on top of chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; add remaining cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: dutch potato soup
directions: Saute onion in oil in large kettle.
Add cumin and chives. Boil potatoes in just enough water to cover them.
Simmer until tender.
Add milk to onion; bring just to a boil.
Add cooked potatoes.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Top with chopped parsley.

title: breakfast special
directions: Grease a 3 qt. rectangular baking dish; set aside.
In a very large skillet cook sausage and onion until sausage is no longer pink and onion is tender; drain off fat.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine 5 c. of the cereal and cooked rice.
Spread rice mixture evenly in bottom of prepared baking dish.
Spoon sausage mixture over rice layer, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
In a medium bowl beat eggs, soup, and milk with a wire whisk until combined; carefully pour over layers in baking dish; press down lightly with back of spoon.
Toss remaining 1 c. cereal with butter; sprinkle over the top.
Bake in 325° oven 50 - 55 minutes; let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: punjabi appetizer dip
directions: Combine the salad dressing, horseradish, vinegar and curry powder, blending until smooth.
Serve with cauliflowerets.

title: cinnamon raisin bread
directions: In small saucepan, heat milk until bubbles form around edge of pan. Remove from heat. Add 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1/2 cup butter. Stir until butter melts.

Add mashed potatoes. Cool to lukewarm. If possible, check temperature of water with thermometer. Sprinkle yeast over water in large mixer bowl; stir to dissolve. Add milk mixture and 3 1/2 cups flour; beat with electric mixer until smooth, 2 minutes. Stir in raisins. Gradually add remaining flour; mix by hand until dough is stiff and leaves sides of bowl. Turn dough onto lightly floured pastry cloth or board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 10 minutes.
Place in greased large bowl.
Turn dough to bring up greased side.
Cover with towel. Let rise in warm place (85°), free from drafts, until doubled in size (1 1/2 hours).

title: virginia apple cake
directions: Mix oil with sugar in electric mixer until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla and mix well. Slowly add the sifted flour mixture.
Add the apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into a tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Combine and mix all ingredients together.
Makes a flaky and tender crust.

title: swiss sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well. Combine sausage and mustard.
Cut bread slices in half.
Space bread evenly in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish (I use Pam). Sprinkle sausage over bread; top with cheese.
Space remaining bread over cheese.

title: milky way candy bar cake
directions: Put chopped candy and 1 stick butter in top of double boiler. Melt and set aside to cool. Cream the sugar, remaining butter and add eggs one at a time.
Heat until light and fluffy. Combine flour and salt; stir in buttermilk along with soda. Alternate flour and milk into butter/egg mixture. Beat well. Add nuts, vanilla and candy bars.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Frost with chocolate marshmallow frosting.

title: cookies & cream
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
Pour in 3 cups milk, add Vanilla Instant Pudding, mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Start with crushed oreos, alternate with pudding mixture. 3 or 4 layers.
Chill 4 hours.

title: whipped potato casserole(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Pare and cook potatoes in salt water until tender (30 to 35 minutes).
Drain, mash and beat in cream cheese and sour cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in garlic salt and garlic powder. Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Heat together in pan oleo, mushrooms, onion juice, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and sherry.
Drain oysters and save 1/4 cup oyster liquid.
Mix beaten egg, oyster juice and cream.
Divide crushed crackers into three parts.
Butter casserole and lay one-third cracker crumbs in casserole.
Layer 1/2 oysters over crumbs and pour 1/2 mushroom mix over oysters.
Repeat 1/3 crumbs, remaining oysters and remaining mushroom mix.
Top with remaining cracker mix and pour oyster juice and cream mix over all.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° to 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.
Stir baking mix and water in pan until moistened; spread evenly.
Spread beef mixture over batter.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a bowl place pudding and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add pineapple tidbits plus juice. Slice oranges and cherries, no juice. Mix all together and chill.

title: grandmother kolowski's polish dumplings
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add farina, salt and enough flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead and form into long roll; cut in pieces. Drop in boiling water.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Melt butter.
Cook onions and bread crumbs.
Pour over dumplings.

title: old fashioned tea cake
directions: Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Sift baking powder with flour.
Mix vanilla with eggs, then mix ingredients in order given.
Make a firm dough.
Roll and cut as desired.
Bake at 400° until light brown (start with 10 to 15 minutes).
Yields 5 dozen.

title: cajun pot roast
directions: Pat roast dry with paper towel.
Rub with peppers and salt. Heat oil in pot over moderate heat. Brown roast on all sides. Transfer meat to plate.
Pour off fat from pot.
Add butter and heat.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic; cook over moderate heat until onion is golden.
Stir flour into pot and stir for 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, beef broth, tomatoes, thyme and bay leaf.
Add meat, bring to boil and then lower to simmer. Cook, covered for 3 hours or until tender.

title: breakfast bundt cake
directions: Grease pan well.
Mix cinnamon, sugar and nuts together and set aside.
Beat cake ingredients 5 minutes.
Pour 1/4 of batter in pan, then a layer of cinnamon mixture, then 1/4 of batter, continuing this until all are used, ending with the batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar and water.

title: pie crust
directions: Can use self-rising flour and omit salt.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake
at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in saucepan.
Add to this mixture 3 well beaten egg yolks.
Add the milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with 3-egg meringue.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: grilled peanut butter and jelly
directions: Make peanut butter and jelly sandwiches.
(Don't use too much or it will run out when sandwich is heated.)
Spread butter on outside of sandwich and grill in skillet until bread is toasted.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and German chocolate, with mixer for 4 minutes.
Fold in grated German chocolate and gradually add chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool before removing from pan.
I sometimes sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar around the top!

title: chicken picado
directions: Brown chicken slices in ovenproof pan.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Saute green peppers over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken back, cook until just done, remove from heat.
Preheat broiler to high.
Top chicken mixture with butter, garlic and cheese.
Place under broiler 6 to 7 minutes, until well browned. Garnish with sliced green onion.
Serve with warm tortillas and Spanish rice.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Combine the dry ingredients alternately add the dry mixture and the banana pulp to the butter, sugar, egg mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Stir in the walnuts.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Beat egg in a bowl.
Crumble bread into it.
Add enough catsup and water to make a soupy mixture.
Drop in the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Brown in small amount of oil in frypan.
Remove to casserole dish.

title: toll house peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, peanut butter, both sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 6 ounces (1 cup) chocolate chips.

title: eleanor's hot fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
If mixture is too thick, add a little more milk.
Mint flavoring also may be added.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per package.
Pour half the batter into a greased/floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, melt caramels, butter and milk in saucepan over low heat.
Stir constantly.
Pour this over half baked cake while cake is hot.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans.
Then pour on the remaining batter.
Bake for another 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not underbake.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Beat heavy cream until very thick; set aside.
Cream together sugar and cream cheese; add vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Top with pie filling of your choice.

title: dad's meat loaf
directions: Chop green pepper and onion fine; mix all ingredients, except reserved tomato soup, and put into baking dishes (at least 9 x 13-inch).
Top with reserved tomato soup.
You can garnish with green pepper slices.
Bake at 350° about 2 hours.
This meat loaf makes its own gravy-like sauce that tastes great over mashed potatoes.

title: hot fudge
directions: Melt together 1/2 square chocolate and 1/2 cup oleo.
Add other ingredients and stir to a slight boil and enjoy.

title: cheese burger soup
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Finely chop celery, carrots and onion and saute with 2 Tbsp. butter until tender.
Add chicken broth, half cup of water, diced potatoes, parsley flakes, and beef. Bring to boil then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix together in the saucepan the flour, salt and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it boils.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin.
Cool.
When partially set, beat with rotary beater until smooth and blend in vanilla and almond extract. Gently fold in stiffly beaten whipping cream.
Carefully fold in a meringue of the egg whites, cream of tartar and sugar.
Fold in coconut and pour into a 9 or 10-inch pie crust.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: cornmeal gravy
directions: Mix together cream, water and salt.
Heat grease in an iron skillet on medium to low heat.
Mix in cornmeal until well coated in grease.
Stir constantly until meal begins to brown.
When meal browns slightly, pour in cream mixture and turn burner up to medium-high until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly until gravy begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and serve with fried potatoes.

title: pat's rolls
directions: Heat together first 4 ingredients until butter melts. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to warm mixture.
Stir in flour until stiff.
Knead lightly, adding more flour, if necessary.
Let rise in bowl 15 minutes.
Punch down.
Shape into rolls.
Place on greased sheet.
Let rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Takes about 1 1/4 hours altogether.

title: creamed asparagus
directions: Heat together soup and butter.
Add chopped hard-cooked eggs. In a small baking dish, put layer of cracker crumbs, layer of asparagus, then soup mixture.
Continue with layers of each and top with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot through and through.

title: joggin in a jug
directions: Mix. Refrigerate. Drink 2 ounces each day.

title: cracker torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually beat in sugar.
Fold in baking powder and vanilla.
Fold in crackers, nuts and cherries. Place in a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with sweetened whipped cream and chill for at least 3 hours or omit whipped cream and top with vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water; bring to a boil.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add jello and butter; blend well.
When cool, add strawberries and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring oleo, sugar and syrup to hard boil stage (260°).
Boil for 5 minutes and then add soda. Mix well. Pour over popcorn and mix. Bake at 250° for 1/2 to 1 hour, checking every 15 minutes.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix altogether except butter and vanilla.
Cook about 20 minutes and add butter.
Cook until candy forms into little balls in cold water.
Add vanilla and beat until it starts to harden and pour into plate and let cool.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch.
Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of prepared shell.
Pour filling over bananas.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with banana slices.
Spread whipped cream over top.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until fluffy.	Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake until lightly brown at 350°.

title: holly sandwich wreath
directions: Unroll pizza dough.
Place dough side by side on a baking sheet with two short sides touching, pinch to seal.
Cut a 2 inch strip from one short side; set aside.
Brush the remaining dough with salad dressing to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Top with turkey, cheese, red pepper, and onions.
Roll up, jelly roll style, starting with a long side; pinch seam to seal.
Place seam side down on an ungreased baking sheet; form a ring and pinch ends together.
Beat one egg yolk,
brush over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine broth, oil and vegetables in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in chicken soup, chicken and pepper.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: egg nog for 12
directions: Beat yolks of eggs well; add sugar and beat well. Slowly add bourbon 1 tablespoon at a time. Fold in whipped cream. Beat whites of eggs until they stand; fold in slowly. Sprinkle nutmeg over the top.

title: zucchini casserole #1
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cottage cheese, eggs and spices in blender.
Saute mushrooms and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Cover with remaining grated cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
For best flavor, make a day ahead.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
May garnish just before serving with crisp-cooked crumbled bacon.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Do not use mixer.
Mix well and add flour with cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan delights
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Drop from a teaspoon on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: bao zier's thai red curry
directions: *Available at Apsara-Oriental Gourmet Market in Herndon.

title: emerald salad dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 2 cups; bring to boil.
Add gelatin to boiling syrup and stir to dissolve.
Add drained pineapple; pour into 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch dish.
Cover immediately with a layer of marshmallows.
Chill until gelatin is firm.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Heat
oven
Grease round 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Mix butter, pudding mix, oil, sour cream and eggs altogether. Bake for
about an hour until brown.
Take it out of the oven and
let it	cool
before
you turn it out of the baking pan. Finally
put your
icing
on it and then put sprinkles on it. It's finished and ready to eat.

title: ribbon pumpkin bread
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sugar, flour and egg whites in a bowl; set aside.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Leave plain or glaze.

title: bob hall's microwave scottish haggis
directions: Cook the liver medium and grind fine in a meat grinder or food processor (or have store grind it while frozen!)
Cook the sausage and lamb medium, drain grease and break up into small bits.
Mix all ingredients very well in a large microwave cooking dish.
Micro on High for 30 plus minutes, stirring every 10 minutes so a crust doesn't form on the outside, until done through.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; put in an 8-inch pie plate. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cover with whipped cream to serve.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and margarine.
Mix in dry ingredients, then add chocolate chips and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or more.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 16-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: three-way beef loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press half of the mixture into an ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Spoon remaining mixture into ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch. Pat into an oblong shape, about 10 x 6-inches.
Cut oblong into 1-inch squares; separate squares.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Divide squares into two 1-quart freezer containers.
Cover and label.
Freeze up to 2 months.
Bake beef loaf in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with catsup.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Remove kernels from cobs.
Mix corn and flour.
Blend in salt, pepper and egg yolks.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into corn mixture.
Cover bottom of a large skillet with oil.
Heat until a drop of water sizzles. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into skillet.
When browned on bottom, carefully turn and brown on the other side.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello cut-out cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar, add Jello and eggs, and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine all ingredients together.
Form into ball or brick and refrigerate several hours - overnight is best.
When ready to cut out, roll out on slightly floured surface, and cut out using favorite cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool and frost or decorate to your desire.
At Christmas time, using red and green Jello and using Christmas cookie cutters, they are good, healthy, and pretty even without frosting.

title: hot buttered coffee
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add ice cream, beating well.
Spoon mixture into a freezer-proof container and freeze.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Prepare Streusel Topping.
Reserve.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Beat 30 seconds.
Spread in pan. Sprinkle with Streusel Topping.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
In skillet, brown meat, mushrooms and onion in butter or margarine.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Add broth.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Gradually blend 1/4 cup water into flour; slowly add to sauce. Cook; stir until thickened.
Slowly blend in sour cream; heat. Serve over noodles with salad and bread.

title: tallerine
directions: Saute onion and garlic in small amount of oil; add meat and chili powder.
Stir until brown.
Add noodles, soup, water, salt, pepper and corn.
Place in large casserole dish.
Place grated cheese on top.
Cook until bubbly at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain and squeeze spinach.
Mix all ingredients well and chill to set (minimum of 2 hours).

title: kathryn's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix according to package directions.
Pour into 4 (6 ounce) dessert glasses.
Add whipped cream and serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Cool and add soda.
Cream together sugar, eggs and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator.
It will keep up to 6 weeks.
Do not stir!
Spoon into greased tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This will make 12 dozen muffins.

title: buttermilk-cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, sugars, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and ginger.
Stir in oil until crumbly.
For cake topping, pat 3/4 cup flour mixture into a small bowl.
Stir in nuts and remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Stir baking soda and baking powder into remaining flour mixture.
Beat buttermilk and egg to blend.
Add to flour mixture.
Pour into pan and sprinkle nut mixture on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Cool.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate and Crisco over hot water.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add chocolate/Crisco combination. Spread on greased cookie sheet (small) or a greased pizza pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
When cool, frost with Jiffy mix white frosting.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until thick and foamy. Add
sugar gradually and continue beating until stiff. Add vanilla (a few drops of food coloring adds a festive touch for Christmas
cookies,
St.
Valentine's
day or Easter time; otherwise the cookies will be white).
Stir in nuts and chips. Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Drop onto foil in small peaks.
Put cookies
in
oven
and
turn
off
oven.
Leave in closed oven several
hours
or
until oven is completely cool. (Do not leave oven light on or cookies will be sticky.)

title: finger salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1 bottle Italian dressing and allow to marinate several hours or overnight.
Delicious.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine the crabmeat, cheese, olives, scallions, celery and seafood seasoning in a medium-size bowl. Add mayonnaise to moisten. Chill 1 to 2 hours. Top with chopped parsley and serve. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: vanilla cream pie(basic recipe)
directions: Mix
sugar, flour and salt in Teflon skillet.
Add milk and cook
until
thick,
stirring constantly.
Add beaten egg yolks and butter and cook for 2 minutes.	Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and pour into a cooked pastry shell.

title: round steak chop suey
directions: Toss meat
in
nonstick
pan
or in small amount of fat until it	browns.
Add
soups
with water and soy sauce.	Cook meat on low
heat or in a 325° oven until almost tender (about 30 minutes).
Add
celery.
Cover.
Cook gently for 30 minutes or until
done.
Blend
flour and water; add to thicken.
Heat until boiling
point
and
cook until thick.
Add drained bean sprouts and
mushrooms.
Heat through.
Serve on rice or crisp noodles. Serves 6.
Freezes well.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain. Mix together the corn meal, eggs, milk, baking powder, salt, corn and chile. Pour 1/2 of batter in greased casserole dish, all of the meat and grated cheese. Put remainder of batter on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes. Recipe can be doubled.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: Brown beef, garlic and ginger over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
In same skillet, heat oil over medium heat until hot.
Stir-fry pepper and peas until tender-crisp, 3 minutes.
Add rice, soy sauce and sesame oil; mix oil.
Return beef, heat through 5 minutes.
Stir in green onions.
Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: sue's chicken marsala (easy)
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and flour.
Melt margarine in pan.
Saute chicken until lightly browned (2 minutes each side).
Remove chicken to oven dish.
Add following to frying pan:
Marsala wine, chicken soup and enough flour to thicken.
Add mushrooms; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Place over chicken and place in 325° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup of pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Form into a ball and roll in 1 cup of pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 tablespoons butter in saute pan.
Add mushrooms, sauteing about 3 minutes.
Reserve.

title: veal and peppers
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook garlic until browned; discard.
Add the sliced onions and peppers; cook 2 minutes, stirring.
Stir in vinegar, basil, oregano, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 10 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove vegetables to medium bowl.
Keep warm.
With meat mallet, pound cutlet until 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
On waxed paper, coat cutlets with flour.
In same skillet over medium-high heat, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Cook meat a few pieces at a time, until lightly browned on both sides, adding more butter if necessary.
When all veal is cooked, arrange the meat with the peppers and onions on a warm platter or serve in skillet.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 and grease 13 x 9 baking pan.
Mix all the above ingredients together in a large bowl with an electric mixer on low speed until well blended.
Pour cake into baking pan, and bake for about 30 minutes or until cake is done in a 350 oven.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together in bowl, then mix oil, sugar, vinegar and oregano until all mixed up; pour over vegetables.
Let sit overnight before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Batter will be soft like cake batter.
Drop in muffin pan and bake at 375° until done.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; set aside.
Beat eggs, then add oil; mix well.
Add
mashed sweet potatoes, pecans and raisins.
Stir until blended.
Stir in milk.
Bake at 350° in loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: million-dollar pound cake
directions: In bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour, and mix until blended after each addition. Stir in almond extract and vanilla.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers fine.
Add garlic, coriander, parsley, salt and vinegar.
Stir and chill in covered dish.

title: mushroom-onion soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in butter in a heavy 4-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato paste; simmer about 1 minute.
Add broth, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; simmer 1 hour.
Serve with croutons and additional cheese, if desired.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Then alternate sour cream and flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a "slightly greased" 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar and apple cider vinegar.
Pour over shredded cabbage; toss to coat.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp; keep drippings in pan. Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef; mix well on foil.
Pat meat to 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham atop.
Top with shredded cheese. Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using foil to lift.
Seal edges and ends.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
(Center will be pink.)
Halve cheese diagonally.
Place atop roll.
Return to oven until melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in warm water, drain.
Melt butter in pan.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until it looks like cornmeal.
Beat egg slightly.
Add vinegar and water.
Gradually add egg mix to dry ingredients.
Mix enough to hold dough together. Work on wax paper.
Keeps for a week in refrigerator.
Can be frozen indefinitely.
Makes 3 to 4 single shells.

title: kim's seafood pasta
directions: Melt butter in saute pan.
Add garlic, shallots, tomato and onion.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add shrimp and scallops.
Cook until shrimp and scallops are slightly firm.
Add crab and cooked pasta spirals.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring the whole time.
Add heavy cream and allow to simmer until reduced in half.
Add cheese and pepper.
Mix well and serve immediately.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Grease bread pan (any size or style). Mix dry ingredients (all but sugar); make well in center of dry ingredients.
Combine egg, mashed bananas and oil together.
Add to dry mixture and stir until moist; may be lumpy.
If desired, add nuts (I don't).
Pour into prepared pan or pans and bake at 350° until toothpick is clean when inserted into center; cool.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn meal and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oranged walnuts
directions: Mix sugar, orange juice and water.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add walnuts, orange peel and salt.
Mix until cloudy.
Quickly place on waxed paper and separate clumps with 2 forks.

title: honeycutt's texas chili
directions: Cook first 8 ingredients for 1 1/2 hours.
Add chili blend and flour.
Cook and stir for 10 minutes more.
Pour in pan and let cool until sets up.
Cut in blocks, wrap, then freeze.
This makes about 20 pounds of chili.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add salt, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until easy to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Press 1/2 candied or maraschino cherry in each.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: halibut au gratin
directions: Place halibut in casserole dish.
Dust flour over fish. Sprinkle on needed salt and pepper.
Layer on onion.
Mix cream of celery soup and milk.
Pour over onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Layer on cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: pea pickin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: mexican stew
directions: Saute meat and chopped onion; drain and add to other ingredients. Simmer in large pot for about 15 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and add onions.
Add all other ingredients in crock-pot and simmer for 4 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and cool. Cut ham into thin strips.
Combine macaroni, ham, cheese, celery, green pepper, green onions, pimento and pickle relish.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and salt; add to ham mixture.
Toss lightly. Yield: 6 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add eggs, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll Ritz crackers until fine; add to potato mixture.
Roll corn flakes until fine.
Wrap potato mixture around marshmallows, then roll in corn flakes.
Fry until brown in plenty of butter.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in whipped cream.
Drain liquid from all fruits and fold fruit into pudding with marshmallows and bananas.
Chill.
Serve in lettuce cups or plain.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Combine hash brown potato mix and water; stir well.
Let stand, covered, 15 minutes; drain.
Wrap tortillas securely in aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes as normal.
Let potatoes stand for 5 to 10 minutes after removing from oven.
Halve potatoes lengthwise and carefully scoop out inside. Set shells aside.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove foil and cook for another 30 minutes more or until browned.
Good served with rice.

title: jello popsicles
directions: Use your favorite flavor of Jell-O and Kool-Aid.
Best to use same flavors or like flavors.
Mix the Jell-O, sugar and hot water.
Mix the Kool-Aid and cold water.
Combine the 2 mixtures and pour into popsicle molds.

title: chicken breasts with stuffing
directions: In a glass pan, place chicken breasts.
Top with cream of chicken soup, cheese, then stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Uncover dish the last 15 minutes.

title: salami and cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all
until well blended.
Spread on thin-sliced French bread rounds and broil in oven until heated through.

title: american lasagna
directions: Buy the tenderloin 24 hours in advance before you wish to prepare for marinating.
Have the butcher truss the meat which means that he cuts off the fat and secures it with string for cooking.
Place tender in a large Pyrex bowl to marinate.

title: holiday spaghetti
directions: Cook onion until yellow in 3 tablespoons oil.
Add peppers and mushrooms.
Add ground beef until brown.
Add salt, sugar and tomatoes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise, add green onion, crab and shrimp.
Place in covered container and chill overnight. Makes 1 1/2 cups (18 servings).
Fun to serve with holiday shaped crackers.

title: mayonnaise chicken
directions: Boil chicken in water until done.
Mix chopped eggs and celery with mayonnaise.
Add Miracle Whip.
Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water, then dissolve in hot broth.
Mix all ingredients together and place in Pyrex container or individual molds.
Refrigerate.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt in double boiler the margarine and chocolate chips.
Pour over marshmallows and nuts.

title: crispy cucumber salad
directions: Mix cucumbers, green peppers, onions, salt and ice.
Let set for 2 hours.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Heat, but don't boil. Cool; pour over mixture.
Put in refrigerator and let set overnight.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook 2 1/2 hours at a slow boil.
Put in fruit jars. Delicious served on hot dogs.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli in
salt	water
2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Mix all together.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: indonesian pork
directions: Make kabobs for the grill by skewering the breast of the favorite bird; wrap in bacon.
Add jalapeno, onion and bell peppers to your skewer.
Season with seasoned salt and pepper.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
