Make a well in center and add berries, eggs, oil and nuts.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: honey sesame tenderloin
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and sesame oil.
Pour over pork and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans, soup and seasoning in 2-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Cook at 350° in oven for 40 minutes.
Add onions and cook 10 more minutes.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with margarine and canned milk.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels and milk together; pour over baked layer.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts; top with remaining batter.
(Add a little hot water if too thick.) Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Layer cake pan with apples, then cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Pour melted butter over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: maple pecan tartlets
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, butter, salt and lemon juice. Sprinkle nuts on bottom of each pastry cup.
Add filling and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
May be frozen.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Clean and cut potatoes in half. Place in greased baking pan. Slice onion in rings and place on top of potatoes, then salt and pepper to taste.

title: minted nuts
directions: Cook
slowly
the
sugar,
water,
salt and corn syrup. Remove from
heat just before it forms soft ball when dropped in	cold water.
Add
marshmallows;	stir
until melted.
Add flavoring and nuts; stir to coat.
Turn mixture out onto brown paper
sack. Separate
nuts
and
coating will adhere.
Keeps about a week, or can freeze up to 1 month.

title: yummy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mocha rum balls
directions: Dissolve coffee in rum.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix in a large bowl.
Roll in balls using a rounded teaspoonful of mixture for each.
Store in tightly covered container for several days.
Then roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen Rum Balls.

title: vanilla pops
directions: In a blender, combine ingredients; cover and process until smooth.
Pour into Popsicle trays or small disposable cups.
If using disposable cups, insert a craft stick into the middle. Freeze until firm, about 5 hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour, yeast and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Heat milk, water, oil and honey over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add the liquid and egg to flour mixture; beat until smooth, about 3 minutes on high speed of electric mixer.
Gradually stir in more flour to make a soft dough.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Stir over heat.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, flour with baking powder, nuts and chips. Mix all by hand.
Grease cookie sheet with margarine.
Spread batter into pan.
May have to spread by hand dipped in flour. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares when cool.
May be sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: fabulous fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chips with margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, sweetened milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chips.
Turn into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool; cut into bars.
Store, tightly covered, at room temperature.

title: old fashioned gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, molasses and eggs. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Roll into walnut size balls and cost with sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oreo delight
directions: Thaw Cool Whip according to directions on container.
Break Oreo cookies into small pieces.
Fold into Cool Whip, along with chopped pecans.
Serve in parfait glasses, topped with a cherry. Serves 8.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, fruit cocktail and juice, coconut, eggs and oil in large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle packed brown sugar and chopped nuts over cake.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool 15 minutes and then glaze.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
In separate bowl, break up lettuce, combine with chopped tomatoes and dorito chips.
Just before serving add browned hamburger meat and onions to lettuce. Add rinsed and drained beans and toss with dressing.
Serve immediately.
8-10 servings.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine zucchini, sugar, eggs, oil and nuts.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices together.
Gradually, add dry ingredients to zucchini mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: corn souffle
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to reserved liquid to measure 1 cup.
Blend flour into melted butter in large saucepan.
Add milk mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into eggs; stir eggs into hot mixture.
Add corn, salt and pepper; mix well. Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set and golden brown.
Garnish with paprika.

title: tomato bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise into 2 halves.
Toast in oven.
Rub garlic cloves over toasted bread.
(Use bread to grate garlic into it.)
Cut tomatoes in half and crush meat of tomato into the bread.
Sprinkle with olive oil and salt.
Grill in oven 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Great with soup or salad.

title: coconut-pecan pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: old time beef stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add 2 c. hot water and seasonings.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaves.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30-45 mins. or until vegs are tender.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Crust:
Mix graham crackers, melted butter and pecans.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Cool.
Beat together 3 eggs, sugar, softened cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread can of blueberry pie filling over cheese layer.
Freeze slightly.
Spread Cool Whip over the top.
Cover with plastic wrap or foil and freeze overnight.

title: tiramisu
directions: Whip cheese, eggs and Amaretto in mixer.
Dip ladyfingers in Espresso and coffee liquor mixture and place in bottom of 11-inch cake pan.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture over ladyfingers.
Repeat a second layer.
Cover the top with cocoa powder.
Serve with whipped cream and chocolate chips.

title: lemon sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well on medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine sour cream and milk and stir until smooth. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in lemon and vanilla extracts.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: "better than wayne" cake
directions: Note:
Also good made with chocolate cake mix, chocolate pudding and chocolate Cool Whip.

title: french onion soup(crock-pot)
directions: Usually, I double this liquid and Worcestershire sauce, not the onions.
If you have a slow cooking pot with a browning unit (I use a frypan), cook the onions in butter until lightly browned.
In the crock-pot, combine browned onions in butter with bouillon, water, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours. Top each bowl with toasted French bread and sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: rocky mountain snow drops
directions: Place chocolate in casserole dish.
Melt in microwave.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add rest of ingredients and mix until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan with crushed Oreo cookies.
Pour melted butter over cookies.
Spread vanilla ice cream on next. Heat together evaporated milk, sugar and unsweetened chocolate. Pour heated mixture on top of ice cream.
Freeze immediately.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Mix all ingredients and separate into approximately 1-inch balls.
Spread balls around bottom and edge of small muffin tins.

title: oatrageous
directions: Mix together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish. Bake on High 4 minutes in microwave.
Turn 1/4 turn and cook 5 minutes longer on High.
Remove and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Wait 10 minutes and spread the melted chocolate.

title: shake and bake mix
directions: Finely crush cracker crumbs.
Mix all ingredients and store in a plastic bag in the refrigerator.
Can be used for baking or frying fish, chicken, pork chops, etc.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: In a serving bowl, layer ingredients in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 10.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Place rice in a baking dish with catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and 2 cups of water.
Saute onions and bacon.
Add to rice.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dave's chili
directions: Combine meat, onions, garlic and green peppers. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chili powder, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and salt. Simmer about 1 1/2 hours. Before serving, add kidney beans and heat thoroughly.

title: baked salmon patties
directions: On a large double thickness square of foil, place a 1/4 pound hamburger patty. Surround with potatoes, carrots and onions. Salt and pepper to taste. Add a pat of butter if desired. Fold foil and seal ends. Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes. Make 1 package for each person.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine pudding mix with 4 cups milk in large mixing bowl. Mix well.
Stir in vanilla, condensed milk, sugar and strawberries.
Add enough food coloring to obtain desired tint.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges through coarse blade of food grinder.
Add sugar and let stand for 2 hours.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Blend remaining ingredients with fruit mixture; add dry ingredients and mix just until flour is moistened.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans which have been greased, lined with wax paper, then greased again.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil to help prevent loaves from cracking on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil; continue baking about 40 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Peel off paper and cool. Can freeze or keep in refrigerator.
Tastes better after it stands for awhile.

title: squash casserole(award winning recipe)
directions: Boil chicken, debone it and cut in pieces. Combine all ingredients and cook on low for about 30 minutes. Pour into sprayed casserole dish, top with cheese and stuffing. Bake about 30 minutes or until bubbly. Do not cover.

title: captain jim's gourmet alaska smoked salmon dip
directions: Warm cream cheese to room temperature.

Add the salmon (including skin and oil) and mix with cream cheese using a fork. Shape into a ball and let stand for a few hours to blend flavors. Ground nuts or finely chopped parsley may be added for garnish.

title: screw salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In blender puree cucumber, onion, mustard, salt, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over noodles.
Best made the night before so juices can soak into noodles.

title: pepperoni pizza spread
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 9 ingredients.
Transfer to an 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers, breadsticks or French bread.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Divide mixture in half and add 1/2 c. coconut and 1 tsp. almond flavoring to one half.
To the other half add 6 oz. chocolate chips and 1/2 c. pecans, chopped.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot and bring to boil.
Serve with chips.

title: snappy beef stew
directions: In saucepan, heat the 2 3/4 cups water to boiling.
Add soup mix, potatoes and frozen vegetables.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Mix flour and the 1/4 cup water.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add meat; heat thoroughly.
Transfer to serving bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: loraine's pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cream of tartar for 5 minutes.
While boiling, add one at a time, 20 Ritz crackers.
Do not stir; pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with butter; cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° approximately 25 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Place half of potatoes in a casserole dish, then cover with a layer of corned beef, then a layer of onion.
Repeat layers.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese browns.

title: surprise pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add Ritz crackers, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Press into metal pie pan and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Let cool until completely cold.
Add bunch of Cool Whip over shell and sprinkle with coconut.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make pudding according to directions, refrigerate.
Bake cake, cool.
Slice cake into 4 layers.
Put 1 layer in large punch bowl.
And bananas, strawberries, nuts, pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip.
Repeat, ending with Cool Whip.

title: chicken-wild rice
directions: Place chicken in a deep kettle.
Add water, sherry, salt, curry powder, onion and celery.
Bring to boil; cover tightly.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat.
Refrigerate chicken and broth at once. When cool, remove from bones.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Use chicken broth to cook rice in.
Follow directions on package of rice.
Combine chicken, rice and mushroom pieces.
Blend sour cream and undiluted mushroom soup.
Toss together with chicken mixture. Arrange whole mushrooms on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Melt margarine and add to first mixture; add vanilla and milk.
For 2 pies, double ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 10-minutes; then at 350° until done.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine; stir in flour.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk; stir until thickened. Remove from heat; add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts; stir in tuna, shells and black pepper.
Heat until hot.
Serve and sprinkle with parsley.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook zucchini, squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in zucchini and onion mixture. Combine stuffing mix according to package directions and spread 1/2 into baking dish.
Spoon in vegetable mixture and spread remaining stuffing mixture over vegetables.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes uncovered.

title: cheddar and vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix eggs and milk, then set aside. Line 8 x 13-inch baking dish with 1 cup buttered cracker crumbs. Layer 1/2 onions, can of soup, 4 ounces cheese, 1/2 onions and top with egg/milk mixture.
Mix remaining crumbs and cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in pineapple and eggs.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart lightly greased casserole dish. Dot with butter and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Wash bass, perch and cod in cold salted water; cut first four ingredients into pieces 1 1/2 to 2 inches thick; set aside.
Rinse shrimp in cold water; set aside.
Heat cooking oil in a 3-quart kettle; add onion and cook until onion is soft.
Add tomatoes, parsley, bay leaf, savory, fennel, saffron, lobster, bass and just enough water to cover.
Season with the salt substitute and pepper.
Bring to boiling and simmer 10 minutes; add perch and cod and continue to simmer 10 minutes longer, or until fish are almost tender.
Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal and onion; gradually beat in milk or water and egg.
Allow to sit 5 minutes.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat where fish was fried.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
(For added flavor, add more chopped onion, 1 tablespoon at a time.)
Makes 20 hush puppies.

title: gold nugget biscuits
directions: Combine cornmeal and milk and let stand 10 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut shortening into flour mixture until it resembles fine crumbs.
Add cornmeal and milk mixture and blend until all ingredients are moistened. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Makes 16 to 18 biscuits.

title: enyucado(columbian)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, butter or margarine and cream cheese in a bowl.
In a second bowl combine instant pudding and milk.
Beat pudding according to directions on package.
Add 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Combine with first mixture.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Place 1/2 of crushed cookies on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour combined mixtures into baking dish.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: tea and fruit cooler
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar in a bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes. Combine all ingredients.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix thoroughly with sour cream.
Add dry ingredients, lemon juice and onion.
Chop shrimp into small pieces and mix thoroughly.
Good! Good! Good!

title: president reagan's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in water until tender; drain thoroughly.
Stir in butter and egg.
Mix salt and mustard with 1 tablespoon water and add to milk.
Add cheese to milk, reserving enough to sprinkle on top.
Pour macaroni into buttered casserole; add milk mixture. Mix thoroughly and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set and top is crusty.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Stir together Crisco, flour and sugar and add enough buttermilk to make a ball.
Knead on a floured surface.
Roll to desired thickness and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° until light brown on top.

title: fat-free banana-crunch muffins
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a medium size bowl.
In a large bowl, using a wire whisk or fork, mix bananas, yogurt, egg substitute and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour mixture just until moistened.
Spray 24 mini muffin pan cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Spoon batter into muffin pan cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tops are golden brown.
Remove from muffin pan to wire rack.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fruit popsicles
directions: Pour fruit and juice into a food mill.
Blend until fruit and juice look like a smooth, thick soup.
Fill a 5-ounce cup with fruit mixture to 1/4 inch below top and place in freezer.
After an hour, when fruit mixture should be partially frozen, put a plastic or wooden spoon or popsicle stick down into the center of each cup.
Return cups to freezer.
In about 3 hours, fruit mixture should be completely frozen.
Take a cup out and warm between hands until popsicle can be pulled out of the cup by the handle.

title: chicken squares
directions: Bone chicken and cut in small pieces.
Simmer onion, peppers and celery in butter.
Add broth, garlic salt, milk and chicken soup.
Put chicken pieces into mixture and cook for 5 minutes. Line large pan with tortillas.
Add a layer of chicken mixture. Top with cheese.
Make 3 layers of each.
Top layer should be cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly and cut in squares.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Pour 1/4 cup oil into glass baking dish, 9 x 13. Mix ingredients. Pour into baking dish and bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes.

title: screwball cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into ungreased pan.
Make a big hole in the center and 2 small holes on either side.
In the big hole, put 2/3 cup salad oil.
In one small hole, 1 tsp. vanilla, in the other small hole, 2 teaspoons white vinegar.
Pour 2 cups water over entire ingredients and mix thoroughly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost as desired. Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Beat in sugar and oil. Add vanilla. Beat until lemon colored. Stir in zucchini, flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder which have been sifted together. Add nuts and pour into greased and floured pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple party rolls
directions: Mix together cream cheese, pineapple, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla. Set aside.

title: sausage bean chowder
directions: Cook pork sausage (casing removed) in skillet until brown. Pour off fat.
In a large kettle, combine kidney beans, tomatoes, water, onion, bay leaf, salt, garlic, thyme and pepper. Add sausage.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Add potatoes and green pepper.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 large or 3 small loaf pans.

title: doran's five minute cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place skillet on stove eye with oil; let skillet get hot.
Mix corn meal, flour, buttermilk and water. Add well beaten egg; mix well.
Pour into skillet.
Leave on stove eye for about one minute.
Place hot skillet on bottom rack in oven for 5 minutes.
Move to top rack and turn on broiler until golden brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Use a large 14 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups milk. Stir in Eagle Brand milk. Fold in 1 carton Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture until everything is used up.
Spread the remaining carton Cool Whip on top. Chill before serving.
Makes a lot and is delicious.

title: sam fye's cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 250° and melt chocolate in saucepan.
Remove from oven, cover and let cool.
Raise oven temperature to 325°. Butter a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Put pan in freezer until ready to use.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Combine cheese, eggs, tuna, onion, pickle, salt, pepper and salad dressing.
Blend lightly.
Split buns lengthwise.
Hollow out inside with fork.
Fill buns with tuna mixture.
Cut into halves.
Wrap each bun in aluminum foil or place buns in baking pan.
Fit aluminum foil over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Mix figs, Jell-O and sugar and bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Place in 1/2-pint sterilized jars and put melted paraffin on top.
Makes 6 jars.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: main dish salad
directions: Cook rice with the salt.
Combine salad greens.
Combine cream and cheeses for dressing.

title: meg's peanut butter chewies
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in a large pan over low heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly. Add Rice Krispies, stirring until cereal is coated.
Pat out in a greased cookie sheet until it is about 1/2-inch thick.
Melt butterscotch chips and chocolate chips over very low heat until mixed together. Spread thinly over top of cookies.
Cut into small pieces, as these are very rich.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions;
drain.
Add tomato soup, beans and corn.
Pour
into
large casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes (seasoned well).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and rolls for complete meal.

title: matt's prize winning steak sprite delight
directions: Flour and brown steak in 1/4 cup oil.
Drain then put back in pan.
Mix all sauces together and pour sauces and Sprite over steak.
Add other ingredients; cover and turn down to low; simmer about 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice and serve with apple rings and parsley, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: glow in the dark jello
directions: Make favorite gelatin.
Pour into mold or suitable bowl.
The secret to this special effect is the base on which you will display the gelatin mold.
Take Bundt or angel food cake pan with hollow cylinder center where you insert the flashlight.
Unmold gelatin onto clear transparent glass plate, which will allow light to pass through it and illuminate the gelatin.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Stick holes in top of cake so frosting will run over it.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add pork and beans and taco seasoning.
Put in a square Pyrex baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Make cornbread according to directions on the box.
Add Cheddar cheese to cornbread mixture.
Spread over hamburger mixture.
Bake in oven according to cornbread directions.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Keep chilled until ready to use.
Slice fresh fruit.
For apples, bananas and peaches sprinkle lemon juice over them so they won't turn brown.
Grapes work well also.
Arrange on a platter or chip and dip bowl.
Enjoy!

title: seasoned salt(try this and you'll never buy seasoned salt again!)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
This makes 32 ounces.
Use on roasts, steak, ribs, etc.,	also
in
soup and stews.
Good on scrambled eggs, too!
Makes
great Christmas gifts when put in aluminum shakers tied
with
Christmas ribbon.
Seasons Greetings!

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and nuts.
Blend mayonnaise and whip cream for dressing.
Toss together.

title: bubble rolls
directions: Place rolls in large well-greased cake pan.
Combine pudding and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Heat sugar and margarine to boiling and pour over rolls.
Cover with foil and let rise overnight at room temperature.
Remove foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: taco beef soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned; drain off excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, undrained kidney beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add avocado.
Pass cheese, corn chips and sour cream to top each serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat until fluffy.
Add milk slowly while beating.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; beat.
Pour filling into crust.
Chill several hours; pour on cherries.

title: chewy cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add flour; beat well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of glass in water; gently press each cookie until 2 inches in diameter.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheets before removing to cooling rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple ice cream punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer ingredients.
Chill.
Eat!
This recipe can be doubled or tripled to take to a covered dish luncheon/dinner.
It is always a hit.

title: warm apple crisp
directions: Mix together the apples, 1/3 cup of sugar, cinnamon, salt and melted butter.
Place in greased 8-inch square baking pan; set aside.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: italian stew
directions: Slice peppers, onion, carrots and celery in roaster.
Place steaks, water and Italian dressing in roaster.
Cook at 375° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add egg noodles, uncooked, about 10 minutes before you take out of oven.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend 1/4 pound butter, cream cheese and flour to make pastry dough.
Press small amount into muffin pans.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, except toast.
Crumble toast on top. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and Jello as directed on packages.
Mix all the other ingredients and freeze.
When ready to use
put out 2 to 3 hours ahead of time.

title: cherry angel rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pans with aluminum foil.

title: quick 'n easy gazpacho
directions: Combine vegetable juice cocktail, cucumber, green pepper, onion, celery salt and garlic salt.
Chill several hours.
Stir vegetable juice mixture into milk.
Serve immediately.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sift flour,
salt
and	baking	powder.
Mix
in
1 cup sugar. Stir
in
milk and beat.
Pour this batter over melted butter. Do	not
stir.
Pour peaches mixed with 1/2 cup sugar over this. Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.	Serves 4 to 6. (This cobbler is	served	often
during
peach
season at the Governor's Mansion.)

title: ranch dip
directions: Cream cottage cheese in blender or food processor.
Add dressing mix, mayonnaise, garlic powder and parsley flakes. Chill overnight.

title: glazed strawberry tarts
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in small saucepan.
Add water.
Cook, stirring constantly, 6 to 8 minutes or until mixture is clear and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; cool slightly.

title: karen's coconut pie
directions: Mix in pan and cook until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Pour in baked pie crust.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Put marshmallows in 7-Up; heat (medium heat) until marshmallows melt.
Pour in lime Jell-O (out of the package); mix until Jell-O is dissolved.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add drained crushed pineapple and nuts.
Put in fridge until thickens.

title: pineapple-apricot squares
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in margarine. Mix together sour cream, eggs, vanilla and salt and add to flour mixture.
Knead dough until well mixed.
Divide dough into thirds; pat 2/3 into greased 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan, bringing up around sides.
Add jam, spreading evenly.
Roll remaining dough into a rectangle.
Cut into 1/2 inch strips.
Arrange strips into lattice on top of filling.
Use strips of dough around sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until lightly brown.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: speedy pizza pie
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9 or 10-inch electric skillet generously with shortening.
Add dash of oregano to Bisquick. Combine Bisquick and milk; spread on skillet bottom and 1/4 inch up sides.
Pour sauce over batter and spread to within 1/4 inch of edge of batter.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed. Set control at 300°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove cover last 5 minutes.
Cut in squares and lift out with spatula.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet until done.
Drain; pour into large bowl.
Add chopped onions, 1 cup cheese and the potatoes (drained). Mix together lightly.
Pour soup in saucepan and add just enough water to thin down until mixture looks like gravy.
Heat until warm.
Pour over hamburger, potato mixture.
Mix together and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of cheese over top.
Bake in 325° oven until hot and bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Sprinkle inside bread with garlic salt.
Smear with butter. Add thin sliced onions, then add slices of cheese, then add sliced jalapeno peppers.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° until onions are done and cheese melts.

title: nancy and norma's birthday cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions on box. Remove from oven and poke cake full of holes using the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand over the cake.
Microwave the jar of ice cream topping for one minute and pour over cake.
Cool cake completely.
Spread the cooled cake with Cool Whip.
Grind the candy bars and sprinkle over the top of the cake.

title: (no name candy)
directions: Mix sugar and Karo over low heat to dissolve sugar.
Do not boil.
Mix in peanut butter, then peanuts and cereal.
Spoon out on waxed paper to cool.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well about 2 minutes and bake in greased and sugared Bundt pan at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean. Let cake cool about 10 minutes in pan before turning out onto plate. A glaze is optional.

title: world's greatest meat loaf
directions: Beat egg lightly in medium bowl.
Add salt, pepper, basil, thyme, catsup, mustard and bread crumbs.

title: zucchini omelet
directions: Beat eggs with salt, pepper and cheese. Add the water and beat.
Set aside.
Slice zucchini lengthwise.
Remove seeds and cut up to bite size pieces (do not peel).
Put oil in frypan.
Add zucchini and chopped onion. Fry until tender.
Add egg mixture and allow to set. Turn in plate and return to pan until set.

title: jello salad(low calorie)
directions: Stir cottage cheese, gelatin and pineapple together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans. Mix with mushroom soup. Put into casserole dish and sprinkle with onion rings. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Grease or paper muffin cups. In a skillet, melt butter and saut onion, green pepper and garlic until tender. In large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt and pepper. In a small bowl, beat the milk and eggs together. Add the liquid mixture to the dry along with vegetable mixture, ham and cheese. Stir until moistened. Spoon into muffin cups. Sprinkle sunflower seeds over the tops. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in double boiler.
Combine with remaining ingredients and cook over boiling water about 20 minutes, or until all sugar is dissolved and mixture begins to thicken.
Stir often.
Good warm or cold.
(It will be thick when cold).

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Put cornstarch and sugar and mix.
Blend in milk and other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter in Bundt cake pan.
Pour batter into butter.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes at 352°.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes; slice 1/4-inch thick.
Put into large kettle; cover with water and cook until tender.
Cut shortening into flour and salt, adding enough water to make dough stiff.
Roll out; cut into pieces the size of a cup.
Remove one half potatoes (keep remainder cooking over heat); add 1 cup sugar, one-half butter and part of spices.
Place part of dough over potatoes; top with remaining potatoes.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, remaining dough on top; sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 450° until crust is brown. Remove from oven; place over heat.
Add milk; bring to a boil. Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Yields 16 servings.

title: starter food for sourdough bread
directions: Stir all ingredients into the cup of starter.
You will need a large container, large enough to allow it to double in size as it ferments.
(I use a large plastic container.)
Put starter in refrigerator.
Stir once a day.
Starter will be ready to use in 2 days . Remove from refrigerator.
Let stand at room temperature at least 1 hour.
Stir starter well and measure amount of starter needed for recipe.
Replenish remaining starter with starter food and return to refrigerator.
Use starter 2 to 14 days, stirring daily.
If not used within 14 days, pour off or give away 1 cup . Feed remaining part as if you had used it.

title: deep-dish apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples.
Turn into ungreased baking pan (13 x 9-inch) or glass dish.
Dot with butter.
Unfold pastry over apples.
Fold edges under inside edge of pan.
Bake 1 hour or until juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: kaedjere(india)
directions: Lightly toss all ingredients together with a fork except for the curry sauce.
Blend it in gently at the last.
Pour into buttered 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sieved yolks of 2 hard-cooked eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, dribble melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with split salted almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Peel and slice squash.
Cook squash and onion in water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Fold carrots, squash and onion into soup and sour cream mixture.
Melt margarine in saucepan and stir in stuffing.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Pour vegetable mixture over stuffing.
Top with other 1/2 of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: tuna ring with cheese sauce
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg slightly and set aside 2 tablespoons of egg.
Stir tuna, onion, cheese, parsley and seasonings into remaining egg.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Boil liquid from pineapple with sugar until sugar dissolves, then add pineapple pieces and prepared pudding.
Poke holes over top of cake.
Pour sugar-pineapple mixture over the cake.
When cool, "ice" with the Cool Whip and decorate with cherries.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.

title: golden meatball casserole
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg and salt; mix lightly.
Shape into meatballs; brown in small amount of oil on all sides in large skillet, drain.
Add water, rice, carrots, green pepper and onion. Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix well.
Use a teaspoon and drop into pot with hot cooking oil.
When golden brown, place on a paper towel platter.

title: haystacks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak thinly sliced squash in ice water with 1/3 cup salt for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix syrup and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Put in jars and seal.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Beat sweet potatoes with mixer until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a 9-inch crust (unbaked) and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: roasted potatoes and asparagus
directions: Snap off top ends of asparagus and remove scales.
Combine asparagus and 1 teaspoon of oil.
Toss well in bowl.
Set aside.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat dough into jelly roll pan (slightly greased). Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Frost with cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix fruit and spread on crust.
Will soak crust quickly.
May not use all cherry glaze.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a blender, mix first 5 ingredients slowly (especially the oil; if poured too fat, it will not blend).
Then add onion and poppy seed.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: candied pecans
directions: Blend first two ingredients well; stir in pecans.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour onto buttered foil and let cool.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix everything well, except the eggs.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Put in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mema's favorite 6 cheese lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to the directions. Set aside in a bowl of cold water. Tear wrapping off Italian sausage. Brown Italian sausage and ground beef together. Add onions, peppers and mushrooms and cook until tender. Reduce heat. Add tomato sauce, diced tomatoes and tomato paste. Stir well. Sprinkle garlic powder until it covers top of sauce. Do the same with onion powder and oregano. Lightly sprinkle basil or to suit your taste. Simmer on low 20 minutes. Set aside.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, soda, and cinnamon. Set aside. In a saucepan, place the water,

margarine, oil and cocoa. Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients, mixing well. Set aside. Mix together the buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla. Add to chocolate batter. Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or knife comes out clean.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together, then cream with margarine and eggs, beating well.
Add vanilla, flour, coconut and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Spread marshmallow over cake while hot.
Let cool in pan.

title: cheddar artichoke appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and bread.
Top bread with mixture and add remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 450° until hot and bubbly.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Bring to a boil the water and salt. Pour over raw cleaned pumpkin seeds. Cover and let stand

at room temperature overnight. Drain liquid from seeds. Spread seeds evenly over a baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until seeds are dry and puffed. Stir frequently. Let cool. Store in airtight containers.
Roasted pumpkin seeds stay fresh up to 10 days.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta (firm texture).
Rinse and leave in cold water until ready to use.
Mix carrots, pepper and onions together; set aside.

title: easy cauliflower-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean and cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Steam until they are still a little crisp. Drain and add cream of celery soup and Velveeta cheese; place in casserole dish.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle this mixture over the vegetables and bake 30 minutes in preheated oven.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix salt and flour, then cut in shortening.
Add egg and water and mix well.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll very thin.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drop into boiling broth and cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spritz
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; blend in flour and almond extract. Place dough in cookie press to make the cookie type you want. Best to press out one long strand of dough and cut a piece to form a small round cookie.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no fail wesson oil pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 2 balls.
Roll each ball on floured board or between pieces of waxed paper.
Use for pot pies or other dessert pies.
Bake according to pie recipe.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugar, pepper, vinegar, salt and oil. Mix well.
Set aside.

title: streusel coffeecake
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco oil and egg.
Add milk and beat thoroughly.
Stir in combined dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Spread in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with Streusel Topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and paprika.
Place in a baking dish.
Dissolve chicken bouillon cube in boiling water. Add wine, onion and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes or longer, until tender and golden brown.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Totally mix sugar and cocoa; dump in milk, vanilla and margarine, but do not mix.
Put in microwave about 2 minutes, until butter melts.
Right after you take it out of the microwave, pour in pecans and start mixing.
Pour onto greased dish.
Put in refrigerator.
It is ready to cut in a few minutes.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir in cheese.
Heat through.

title: pie dough
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn down TV.
Remove toys from countertop.
Measure 2 cups of flour.
Get baking powder.
Remove Benjamin's hands from flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Vacuum mixture off kitchen floor (Benjamin spilled). Get an egg.
Answer telephone.
Separate egg and warm Baby Adam's bottle.
Help Mary figure out a new math problem (the old reliable way).
Grease pan; salesman at door.
Take 1/4-inch of salt from greased pan and look for Benjamin.
Put mess in wastebasket.
Put dishes in dishwasher.
Call the bakery.
Take an aspirin.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large pot, pour puree, 3 puree cans of water, tomato paste and spices.
Brown neckbones in a skillet and add to sauce. Simmer several hours until thick.

title: smoked oyster spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; chill.
May be used with crackers or as a filling for tiny sandwiches or with raw vegetables.

title: punch for 50
directions: Mix and serve with crushed ice in it.

title: chocolaty cake pie
directions: Melt chocolate in water; add 2/3 cup sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla. Set aside to cool.
Sift together flour, 2/3 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and beat.
Pour this mixture into pie shell.
Pour chocolate sauce over batter and sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester stuck in center comes out clean. Yield:
8 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup of liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add beets; heat through.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: just for kids goop
directions: Combine salt and 2/3 c. water in saucepan and heat over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cornstarch, 1/2 cup water and food coloring to pan; return to heat and stir. Mixture will thicken.
This is good for modeling because it does not crumble easily.
This has a slightly grainy texture.
Store in an airtight container.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large deep frying pan, cook onions in butter until ???. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raisin custard pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Whisk in the egg yolks and milk until thoroughly combined.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and raisins.
Pour into pie shell.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Take angel food ring and slice into 2 layers (set aside).
Cut strawberries in slices (set aside).
Take softened cream cheese and sugar.
Mix together, then take Cool Whip and mix.
Make icing out of it and cover rings of angel food cake and stack together to make the cake.
Take strawberry glaze and spread over cake.
Put fresh strawberry slices on (cover cake well).
Keep in refrigerator with cover.
Make sure cake is cold before putting on strawberries and jell.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes enough for four cocktails or use over sliced fried wieners.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat or in microwave, melt margarine and chocolate chips; stir in pecans.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack washed cucumbers in sterilized jars. Place remaining ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil. Pour over cucumbers while boiling hot. Seal.

title: chicken veggie bake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and set aside. Place chicken breasts in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Add vegetables. Mix together soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. Top with stuffing mix. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: sangria
directions: Into a pitcher, pour chilled wine over ice cubes.
Combine orange and lemon juices with sugar, add to wine.
At serving time, stir in chilled club soda.
Garnish with the orange peel or float orange slices in the sangria.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or 1 large tube pan.
Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together 3 cups flour and cinnamon.
Mix well with other ingredients, then add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with chips.

title: texas rangers
directions: Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes for chewy, 10 minutes for crispy.

title: chicken delight casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles.
Saute onions in butter until tender; mix all ingredients, except noodles, then gently stir in noodles.
Turn into casserole.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until lightly browned.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese together in a bowl.
Add green chillies, black olives, cheese, onion, salt and jalapeno. Place tortillas in damp paper towel.
Wrap up.
Microwave 2 minutes.

title: plantation supper
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add onion, milk, soup and cream cheese with meat.
Then add corn, peas and cooked noodles.
Stir together and put in casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients and make cake batter.
Stir in milk, vanilla and melted shortening.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into greased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2.
Mix brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Place on cake batter.
Gently pour over this 1 3/4 cups hot water.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: moothart's surprise chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan, cut one tube of chocolate chip cookie dough into 1-inch slices.
Place side by side in pan.
Press dough edges together making a flat surface. Cream together cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Place over cookie dough in pan.
Cut second tube of cookie dough into 1-inch slices. Place side by side into pan.
Do not press together this time. Allow center to cook up through spaces.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: feta and sun-dried tomato torte
directions: Combine butter, cheeses, garlic, shallot, Tabasco and vermouth in food processor; process until smooth.
Line a small bowl with damp cheesecloth, letting edges hang over.
Layer cheese mixture, pine nuts, tomato and pesto in any order until it is all used up, ending with cheese.
Place a piece of plastic wrap on top layer; press gently.
Chill at least one hour, or up to 2 days.
To serve, remove plastic wrap; invert on platter and remove cheesecloth.
Serve with crackers. Makes about 2 cups.

title: deluxe apple pie filling
directions: Bring water and cornstarch to a boil and cook slowly until clear and thick.
Stir in granulated sugar and cinnamon and bring to a boil.
Pour over apples.

title: pistachio and angel food cake
directions: Buy or make angel food cake and slice in 2 or 3 layers.
Mix instant pudding, substituting 1 cup of milk for 1 cup of all-purpose cream or heavy cream.
Frost layers of cake and all around cake.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in order and chill overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef; add all ingredients.
Cook until desired taste.
Serve on hamburger buns with cole slaw and pickles.

title: rich turkey gravy
directions: In medium skillet (medium heat) stir flour into drippings. Cook; stir until dark brown.
Stir in water and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thick and bouillon is dissolved.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat thoroughly. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Chill for ease in handling.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with floured cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Decorate as desired.
Yield:
7 to 8 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice angel food cake into 1-inch thick pieces.
Line a glass baking dish with the slices.
Use hot water and cold water; stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Combine with strawberries.
Then pour over the angel food slices.
Push each of the slices into the Jell-O mixture so they are covered.
They will then rise to the top.
Refrigerate until set.
Cover top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with sliced strawberries (optional).

title: mini sausage quiches
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until creamy.
Blend in flour. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll in 24 (1-inch) balls.
Press each into mini muffin cups.

title: hot diggity hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Cut hot dogs into 1-inch pieces, leaving 4 whole.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam. Combine macaroni, hot dogs (cut) and remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with 4 remaining hot dogs, cut in half lengthwise with 3 small slits cut in top of each.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: wet brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Stir well.
Add flour, salt and chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ground beef salami
directions: Blend all thoroughly, form into rolls 18 inches long and 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Poke holes in foil; place on broiler pan and bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Unwrap to cool.
Wrap in plastic wrap to store.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to package directions; set aside. Melt butter in heavy saucepan; saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in flour; cook over low heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms, broth and half and half. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in rice, chicken, pimiento, parsley and seasoning.
Pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole; top with almonds and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Yield:
About 6 servings.

title: nachos mexican pizza
directions: Grease cookie sheet or pizza pan generously.
Layer ingredients in the order as shown, adding just enough tomato sauce to hold mixture together.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Scramble egg in oil in saucepan, stirring to break into pieces. Add water, soy sauce, scallions and garlic; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir. Makes 4 servings.

title: orange nut cream parfaits
directions: In medium bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and juice concentrate.
Stir in sour cream.
In small bowl, combine coconut, nuts and rind.
Layer filling and coconut mixture in parfait or dessert dishes.
Top with coconut mixture.
Chill in freezer 30 to 45 minutes or 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place milk and pudding in saucepan; cook until thickened. Pour into a large bowl and while pudding is still hot, pour cake mix (as it comes from the package) into pudding.
Mix well and pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chocolate chips over top.
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix soup, paprika, pepper and Mrs. Dash.
Grease casserole dish and place potatoes and ground beef in pan.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes, then spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: lemon yogurt pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into graham cracker pie crust shells.

title: rotel tomatoes
directions: Chop ingredients fine or use a blender; mix together.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Place mixture in hot sterile jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes; makes 6 pints.

title: hot bacon salad dressing
directions: Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Beat egg.
Take bacon and add to salad greens.
Add all other ingredients to beaten egg and pour into the hot bacon fat.
Cook until thick.
Pour at once over 1 quart crisp, dry salad greens like lettuce, spinach and endive.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare, core and slice the apples.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with a pie crust.
Place a layer of apples over the bottom.
Sprinkle with a mixture of the sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add top sheet of pastry and cut slits into it to allow for escape of steam. Flute edges. Bake in a 425° oven for about 50 minutes or until apples are tender and crust a golden brown.

title: easy cherry coffeecake
directions: Spread 2 packages of crescent rolls across the pan width wise on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Mix well.
Spread onto the layer of crescent rolls.
Top with drained fruit and fold over dough so it is not quite touching each other. Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients but soda for 5 minutes.
Stir well. Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Put in 2 flat pans in 250° oven.
Bake 1 hour.
Stir a few times.
Store in tight container.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions.
Drain well.
Combine cooked vegetables, celery, onion, mayonnaise, 1/2 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick chicken 'n dumplings
directions: In 4 1/2-quart kettle, combine chicken, onions (with liquid), carrots (with liquid), green beans (with liquid), chicken broth, barbecue spice, salt and thyme.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix together thoroughly.
Bake one hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: mango salsa(great with salmon or beef tenderloin.)
directions: Whisk jelly and lime juice in large bowl.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Can be made 3 hours ahead.
Marshall Fields has a mild red pepper jelly that is nice to use.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Chop cabbage in large pieces.
Place in bottom of greased casserole dish.
In skillet brown beef and onion; pour off fat. Stir in rice.
Place mixture on top of cabbage.
Cover all with tomato soup and water.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until rice and cabbage are done.
This recipe can be used with sausage, chops or other meats along with the seasoning you prefer.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cut up hen and season generously with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil in heavy pot over medium heat until golden brown.
Remove chicken to large pot or Dutch oven.
Use remaining oil in pot to make roux.

title: deviled egg-ham casserole
directions: Deviled Eggs:
Halve eggs.
Remove yolks; mash with next 4 ingredients.
Refill whites.

title: holiday bean soup
directions: Wash beans, place in large pot, cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain before cooking.
Add 2 quarts water and ham hock or ham quarters.
Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add onion, tomatoes, bell pepper and all other ingredients, including the wine.
Simmer 30 or 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Mix other ingredients.
Make into balls about the size of walnuts.
Dip balls into melted chips.
Chill on waxed paper.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Cut up bananas and put in a large bowl.
Add sour cream and well drained pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Add pecans or walnuts and marshmallows.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and jello.
Stir in oranges and pineapple. Chill 2 hours.
Overnight is better.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Mix other ingredients, except corn flakes or chips.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° in an 8 x 13-inch pan.
When almost done, sprinkle with flakes or chips.
Return to oven until browned.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: elephant ears
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease cookie sheet with shortening.
Heat margarine until melted; set aside.
Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Stir in milk and 3 tablespoons of the melted margarine until dough forms.
Sprinkle a surface lightly with flour.
Turn dough onto surface; knead 10 times. Roll dough with rolling pin, or pat with hands into a rectangle (9 x 5 inches).
Brush with remaining melted margarine, using a pastry brush.
Sprinkle with mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Line metal cake pan with aluminum foil.
Preheat oven to 400°. Put 1/2 stick (more or less) butter on bottom of pan.
Peel and slice potatoes in pan; slice onion on top of potatoes.
Put the rest of the butter on top and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil; place in oven for 1 hour.
Put sliced cheese on top.
Add more butter, if needed.
Place in oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt. Add butter and water.
Blend. Add vanilla.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Combine flour and butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Put over cream cheese layer and refrigerate.
Top with rest of the Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: tabuli
directions: Chop parsley and mint, stems and all.
Place cracked wheat in bowl; cover with warm water and allow to soak for 10 minutes.
All vegetables should be finely chopped.
Drain cracked wheat and squeeze the water out.
Add to the vegetables.
Mix lemon juice, oil and salt.
Pour over the vegetables.
Arrange on a bed of lettuce or serve as pita bread sandwiches.

title: microwave barbecued chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Combine paprika and pepper; rub into chicken.
Arrange chicken pieces in 1 2/3 to 2-quart microwave dish, with meaty portions toward edge.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over chicken.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; add soda.
Grease five #303 vegetable cans using 1 stick oleo.
Add rest of oleo to dates and cool.
Mix sugar and eggs; add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well with the mixture.
Fill cans 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: "galatoboureko"
directions: Custard:
Scald milk and cream; set aside to cool.
Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar and beat well until creamy.
Add farina with a pinch of salt.
Add milk, a spoonful at a time.
Heat, stirring until thickened; set aside to cool.

title: good goblin clusters
directions: Put candy chips in large saucepan (double boiler) and melt slowly over hot water, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles and nuts.
Then drop by spoonful on wax paper and cool.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Let cool slightly.
Add 1 teaspoon soda.
Cream shortening, 1 cup sugar and eggs.
Add salt, flour and 3/4 teaspoon soda; mix together.
Add date mixture.

title: spicy cheese ring
directions: Grate cheeses in large mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Mix with hands and form into ring. Press chopped pecans into ring.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Then add strawberry preserves to center of ring.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: dip - vegetable
directions: Mix all of these ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with a vegetable tray.

title: broccoli spears casserole
directions: Layer broccoli spears and soup in dish.
Top that with a layer of cheese slices.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in 1 cup water and mix with stuffing before putting on top of cheese.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf - complete meal
directions: Mix hamburger, crackers, onion, eggs, salt and pepper and shape by hand.
Cover with ketchup.
If desired, place thin sliced pepper all over top to add flavor.
Spray large roasting pan with cooking oil or Pam.
Place meat loaf in center of pan.
Put potatoes on one end of pan and green beans on the opposite end. Add about 1 inch of water.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Separate into small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise and egg.
Add soups and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased casserole dish.
(Top with remaining cheese before baking.)

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top, then bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chili conqueso casserole
directions: Line the bottom of casserole with crushed up corn chips. Place beans, onions and water in a seperate bowl and mix together. Pour mixture over corn chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 10 or more.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix celery, pepper, onion and English peas.
Stack layer of lettuce, then layer of mixture, etc.
Add the sugar to the mayonnaise; smear on top.
Sprinkle the Parmesan or grated cheese over top.
Sprinkle the bacon bits on top.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix like pie crust and pat in bottom of the pie tin.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil; then simmer for 30 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter; mix well with peanut butter. Add to sifted powdered sugar; mix well. (May add more butter if needed.) Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in double boiler. Pour over peanut butter mixture; cool and enjoy.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up tortillas starting from one side to the other.
Wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 1-inch slices and serve.

title: vegetables au gratin
directions: In a 6-inch round microwavable shallow casserole, layer squash and eggplant.
Cover evenly with onion and bell pepper; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave for 6 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
In a small bowl, combine breadcrumbs, cheese and basil.
Sprinkle evenly over vegetables.
Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave on High for 1 minute, until cheese melts.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in half, slice 1/2-inch thick.
Cut slices into 1-inch strips.
Soak in cold water for 30 minutes. Drain and pat dry.
Dip into batter and fry in deep fryer or pan with 2-inches of shortening.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: bisquick quiche
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese and bacon or ham.
Then put remaining ingredients through blender for 15 seconds.
Then pour over broccoli mixture and bake about 45 minutes at 375°.

title: delicious cherry torte!
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as directed on the package.
Mix softened cream cheese with vanilla pudding.
Beat with beater until smooth. Beat the pint of whipping cream until fluffy.
(I sometimes add Equal or Sweet 'N Low as I beat it.)
Add the whipping cream to the pudding/cream cheese mixture.
In a 13 x 9-inch covered container, put graham crackers, then a layer of the pudding mixture.
(I chip up a banana on the first layer for added flavor or add a layer of crushed drained pineapple.)
Make another layer of graham crackers and another layer of pudding mixture and top with cherry pie filling.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Not good unless it is cold.
Enjoy.
Low-fat and almost sugar free!

title: sugar gem cookies
directions: Combine the sugars, butter, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Beat together until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and in sugar.
Press with a glass that has been greased and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown cookies.
Makes a large batch.

title: lollipops
directions: Note:
You will need waxed paper, pan, wooden spoon, candy thermometer, sticks for lollipops and margarine.

title: potato and watercress soup
directions: In large saucepot, melt butter over medium heat.
Set aside sprig of watercress for garnish.
Add potatoes, the remaining watercress and onion.
Cook, stirring, 5 minutes until onion is tender.
Stir in broth, half and half, pepper and celery seed. Cook over low heat, 10 to 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.

title: green beans amandine
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the green beans, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter. Beat together with the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs. In a bowl, combine flour, bran, oats and baking soda. Stir into butter mixture. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased coolie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender.
Drain and mash, then add all ingredients, except cheese, and mix well.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart baking dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good.

title: lemon lush
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts well.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: mashed potato surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef.
Place in the bottom of a small to medium size glass pan or any casserole dish.
Pour in your vegetables, mix in salt and pepper as needed.
Cover top with mashed potatoes, then sprinkle on paprika.
Cook until bubbly and browned, approximately 45 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, egg yolks and milk.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° in uncooked pie shell until done.

title: fresh tomato juice cocktail
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, green pepper, bay leaf and onion in blender.
Blend thoroughly to puree.
Press through sieve or strainer.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish.
Mix well and chill.
Shake thoroughly before serving.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: helen's veal cordon bleu
directions: Pound meat until 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham and cheese on each piece of cutlet, roll-up carefully, beginning at narrow end. Secure with toothpicks.

title: blueberry ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate, covered, one hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes six servings.

title: butterscotch cherry squares
directions: Beat eggs with rotary beater in top of double boiler just until blended.
Stir in brown sugar and butter.
Place over rapidly boiling water, stirring constantly, until hot or about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add all at once to hot mixture.
Mix well until blended. Stir in chopped nuts and vanilla.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine and spread into a baking dish (8 x 8 preferably) lightly sprayed with cooking spray.
Mix together 2 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup sugar and sprinkle over flour mixture.
Stir well. Pour 1 1/2 cups hot tap water over all.
Do not mix at this point.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy-does-it casserole
directions: In an ungreased 9-inch casserole dish, layer the ingredients in the following order:
extra lean hamburger (raw and crumbled; if fat, cook first and pour off fat), onions to taste, celery soup (can substitute cream of mushroom or chicken) and cheese and top with layer of Tater Tots.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 or more.

title: hot pinwheels
directions: Mix everything together except tortillas.
Spread mixture over tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut rolled tortillas about 1/2-inch thick.

title: beer cheese
directions: Grind or grate cheese finely.
Mix cheese with garlic, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Gradually beat in enough beer until mixture is well blended and of a spreading consistency. Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature with assorted crackers.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Cook beef steak with flour.
Pound into beef.
Brown beef in oil in skillet.
Push beef to side.
Cook and stir in oil until tender.
Drain.
Add enough water to reserved potato liquid to measure 1 cup.
Mix potato liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, green pepper, bouillon, salt, marjoram and pepper.
Pour on beer and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Rinse frozen beans.
Add potatoes, beans and pimento to skillet.
Heat again and cover.
Simmer until beans are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix well ingredients together.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into large glass pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add salt, vanilla and lemon juice; mix well.
Add flour; mix well. Last, add baking powder.
Beat well.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar with cocoa.
Add milk, eggs, margarine and vanilla. Beat well 2 minutes.
Put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
When cool enough to hold, dice potatoes.
Fry bacon crisp.
Crumble.
Add potatoes with salt and pepper.
Heat vinegar and water.
Pour over mixture of potatoes. Heat oil.
Pour over ingredients.
Toss and set aside.
Do not refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature.
This salad must be put together while hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix salad ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, Bran Buds, sugar and soda.
Beat milk, egg, molasses and butter together.
Combine dry and liquid mixtures together with a few swift strokes.
Fold in dates or raisins and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine.
Put meat loaf in pan for about 10 minutes.
Cut into quarters.
Turn over.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes more, then turn heat to low and cook for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Tear broccoli florets into bite size pieces in large bowl. Add cheese, pimento and dressing mix.
Add enough mayo to combine and hold salad together.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: booze wieners
directions: Cut in small pieces.
Cook in fondue pot in glaze until cooked down.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in freezer for about 15 minutes.
Roll on waxed paper in chopped pecans and form ball. Store in refrigerator.

title: dressed eggs
directions: Peel eggs and take the yolks out.
Mash up.
Put all the ingredients into the yolks and mix well. Add enough salad dressing to mix well.
Put the yolks back into the eggs.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Put into refrigerator until cool.

title: hot garlic-cheese loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine baking mix, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add milk and eggs to dry ingredients; mix only until ingredients are moistened.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Prepare dough and let rise.
Turn out on floured surface. Divide into thirds.
Pat each into greased 8 x 13-inch round pan. Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Sprinkle 1/3 of topping over each coffee cake.
Cover and let rise until double (30 to 45 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
You can ice with confectioners sugar icing.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine peas, beans, corn, onion, celery and pimientos.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves. Pour over the vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt margarine, pour over nuts and let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Mix milk, sugar and coconut; then add the nut mixture.
Mix well and chill 2 hours.
Form into small balls and refrigerate overnight.
Melt 1/4 pound paraffin and 12 ounce package chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip and place on waxed paper.

title: new world tzimmes(jewish sweet potato casserole)
directions: Cook or bake potatoes in their skins until tender, but firm. Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in skillet until it foams.
Add carrots and saute until nearly tender.
Add apples and saute until a bit soft.
Peel sweet potatoes and cut into large dice; place in bowl.
Combine sauteed carrots and apples with remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into oiled deep casserole dish; cover and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Make tiny meatballs and fry gently, draining grease.
Mix chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in pan.
Add meatballs and simmer for 20 minutes or until hot and well blended.

title: molded cranberry-nut salad
directions: Cook cranberries in boiling water for 10 minutes. Add sugar and salt.
Cook an additional 10 minutes. Add gelatin which has been soaked in the cold water.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill the jello and when it is about to set, stir in celery and nuts. (Drained, crushed pineapple may be added, if desired.)
Pour into a wet mold and chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter in jelly roll pan.
Spread crushed graham crackers over the butter.
Sprinkle chips, coconut and nutmeats on in layers.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Dough should be stiff.
Mix together and roll in small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool and frost with powdered sugar icing, if desired.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Parboil shells per directions.
Chop garlic and onions finely. In blender or food processor, blend crackers to make crumbs. Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients together.
Drain shells.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Put down in single layer on top of 1/2 jar of sauce in bottom of dish.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: baked onion dip
