directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare a 2 qt. baking dish with cooking spray. In a large mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, onions and cheese. Pour the mixture into the baking dish and bake for approximately 45 minutes, until the top is slightly brown. Serve hot with Ritz crackers.

title: yogurt-creamed oats with fruit
directions: Soak oats in 5 tablespoons warm milk until swollen, about 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt, hazelnuts, honey and lemon juice.
Mix grated apples into yogurt mixture. Carefully mix in 1 pint mixed berries. Spoon mix into each of 4 goblets or bowls.
Garnish with thin apple slices and mint sprigs.
Serves 4.
For breakfast, brunch or dessert.

title: icebox dream layer cake
directions: Split each cake in 1/2 to make a total of 4 layers.
Whip the cream, adding sugar until stiff.

Slowly beat in Hershey's syrup. Spread whipped cream between layers and on top and sides of cake. If desired, garnish with grated or shaved semi-sweet chocolate. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Mix oil, garlic, soy sauce and lemon juice; set aside.	Score meat on both sides.
Baste with lemon mixture and place on hot grill.
Partially cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes per side.	Turn 3 or 4 times, basting occasionally, and season with salt and pepper. For indoor baking, preheat oven to 350°.
Baste and place pork chops on racks on baking sheet.
Bake about 30 minutes, turning and basting with lemon mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: very special meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, peanuts, celery leaves, parsley, green onions, eggs, tomato paste, lemon juice, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Shape mixture into a loaf and place in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with green pepper rings during the last 20 minutes of baking.
Serves 8.

title: copper mountain chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Remove cake from oven and poke holes over surface with wooden spoon handle. Combine condensed milk and caramel topping; pour over hot cake. Cool and refrigerate several hours. Stir crushed candy bars into whipped topping and spread over cake. Store in refrigerator. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Mix together margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Press into 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Mix cream cheese with 3 eggs and sugar together.
Pour over cake mix mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients very well. Cover & chill for several hours before serving. Serve with raw vegetable, crackers or baguette.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and water until cranberries are done.
Add sugar and cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour over jello.
Cool.
Add celery, apples, nuts and salt.
Mix with cooled cranberries and jello.
Mold.

title: tomato-mozzarella salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and cheese.
Sprinkle with basil.
Chill before serving.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Melt stick of margarine.
Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and salt.
Remove ends from bread. Mix in pineapple and bread. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate date loaf
directions: Pour water over dates and cool to lukewarm.
Cream butter and sugar together; add egg, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Add cooled dates, then add flour, soda and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 1 large breadpan loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package. Rinse with cold water until cool. Drain.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: cream pudding(flotegrot)
directions: Boil cream 10 minutes or until it stops foaming.
Stir in 3 tablespoons flour or enough to make a thin porridge.
The fat will now separate.
Remove kettle from heat and set aside for 3 minutes with the cover on.
Remove fat.
The kettle may be placed over heat again, if desired, to remove more fat.
It also helps to put a couple of spoons of cold water in the kettle.
Remaining flour is now sifted into the mixture, then hot milk is stirred in gradually. Cook until slightly thick.
Salt is added when pudding is cooked. Serve with sugar, cinnamon and the hot fat.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Heat mixture to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir once or twice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange apricot ring
directions: Drain apricots; puree in blender.
Add enough water to syrup from apricots to make 1 1/2 cups.
Combine syrup and gelatin; heat to boiling to dissolve gelatin.
Add concentrate; stir until melted.
Stir in apricot puree and water.
Pour into 5-cup mold and chill.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix and cook water, cornstarch and sugar until clear. Add Jell-O and mix well. Cool. Add strawberries.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over chicken wings and marinate for several hours.
Pour into ovenproof pan (13 x 9-inch glass is fine).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until browned.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef, onion, and green pepper over medium to high heat for 7 to 9 minutes, drain off the excess liquid.
Add the tomato sauce, sugar, garlic powder, salt, and pepper; mix well.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on the buns.

title: speedy shrimp sauce
directions: Just mix in blender or shaker and serve over your favorite fish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Use a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Melt butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour cake mix batter over coconut, then cream cheese mixture over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, add water, margarine and cocoa.
Bring to boil.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground beef in a skillet; drain fat.
Drain mushrooms. Add all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Mix zucchini, onion and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard, turmeric, nutmeg, celery seed and cornstarch. Mix all together.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour in sterilized jars.
Seal at once.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Place in mixing bowl the flour and sugar.
In saucepan, mix cocoa, margarine, Coca-Cola and marshmallows.
Bring to boil and pour into mixing bowl; mix well.
Combine buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Beat and add to mixing bowl.
Put in 11 x 14-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: marian's blessed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes until tender.
Cool.
Grate into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: seafood rotelle
directions: In 4 tablespoons margarine, cook onion until limp.
Blend in flour and stir until bubbling.
Remove from heat; stir in broth, clam juice, wine, yogurt, oregano, red pepper, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Stir until thick and the cheese has melted.
Add shrimp and crab.
Pour over rotelle.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Cook shrimp.
Combine with crab, celery, pepper and onion. Mix mayonnaise with Worcestershire sauce and salt and fold in crab mixture.
Spread in buttered 2-quart baking dish or into 6 (1-cup) casserole dishes.
Bake in 400° (hot) oven for 10 minutes.
Blend potato chips with paprika.
Sprinkle over seafood mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes more until potato chips are browned.
Serves 6.

title: italian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine the soup, water and prepared dressing.
Set aside.
Arrange the peas, carrots and potatoes around chicken.
Pour the dressing and soup mixture over all the ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until chicken is done and tender.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours; high for 6.
Serve on grilled hard rolls with pepperoncinis.

title: mom's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt. Combine brown sugar and butter in an eight inch skillet or cake pan and stir over low heat until blended well. Arrange fruit on brown sugar mixture, placing fruit cut side up. Slowly stir white sugar into egg yolks, adding hot water slowly and beat well. Add vanilla and dry ingredients mixing well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into above batter. Pour batter carefully over fruit, bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes. While still hot, invert onto a serving platter.

title: strawberry, cranberry, pineapple salad
directions: Drain the pineapple well.
Put the juice with water to make 3 cups.
Boil and pour over the jello and mix.
Add cranberry sauce; mix.
Add pineapple and box of strawberries.
Stir now and then until everything is thawed and mixed.
Let set.

title: "sweet and savory" morning muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine carrots, apples, coconut, raisins and nuts.
In third bowl, combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Pour over carrot-apple mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and stir just until mixed.
Do not beat.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine all ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
Grease cake pan and pour contents into pan.

title: vince's ham glaze
directions: Cook the ginger ale and 1 pound brown sugar until syrupy.
Add the mustard and cook a couple of minutes (it will make tiny lumps).
Pour on a whole ham and put in oven to bake.
About 1 hour before ham is done, pour off the broth and add the juice of pineapple and more brown sugar.
Cook this until it makes a thick syrup.
Put pineapple slices on your ham.
Add the glaze and bake until done.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O. Add pineapple and let stand until it starts to set. Add cheese and pimiento which have been mixed together. When mixture begins to harden, add nuts and whipped cream.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Clean and cut potatoes in thin slices.
Boil potatoes about 5 minutes to partially cook.
Melt butter over medium heat and blend in flour and salt.
Add milk slowly.
Cook until smooth and boiling.
Reduce heat and add cheese.

title: orange smoothe
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend on high speed until all ice cubes are crushed.

title: vegetarian dinner cut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Cool for at least 3 hours or overnight before attempting to slice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Just mix all ingredients well.
Chill, if you want, but not necessary.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: apple strueffel
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Arrange in deep baking dish or casserole.
Sprinkle cup of white sugar mixed with the cinnamon over the apples.
Mix brown sugar, flour and butter well.
Spread over apples and bake about 45 minutes.

title: snow-white decorator icing
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Then add cornstarch, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Whip until fluffy (2 minutes).
If icing is too thin, add powdered sugar as desired.
Yield is approximately 4 cups.
Food coloring may be added for desired color.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Pack into bowl lined with wax paper to make a roll, which is especially nice for easy slicing.
Chill.

title: frozen mud pie
directions: In a bowl, combine crushed cookies and sugar. Stir in butter. Press onto the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Spoon 1 pint of ice cream into crust. Drizzle with half of the chocolate syrup. Swirl with a knife. Carefully top with the remaining ice cream. Drizzle with remaining syrup. Swirl with a knife. Cover and freeze until firm. Remove from the freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Garnish with whole cookies, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Grind all the fruit (I use a food chopper).
Mix all the fruit well, then add the spices and sugar.
Stir to mix well, then cook for about 2 hours, stirring often to keep from scorching.
Can while hot.

title: mushroom pate
directions: Clean and slice the mushrooms.
Cook in the butter for 2 minutes.
Puree in a blender until smooth.
Add cream cheese and garlic powder; blend well.
Chill and serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: ranch beans
directions: Drain bean liquid and throw away. Add catsup, sugar, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, onion and mustard.
Put 4 slices bacon on top and bake in casserole at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: raspberry almond cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium size saucepan, combine raspberries, water, 4 tablespoons honey and tapioca; set aside. In a medium size bowl, stir together flour and baking powder.
Cut in 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in almonds.
In a small bowl, combine buttermilk, egg and the remaining 1 tablespoon honey.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Bring raspberry mixture to boil; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter and the almond extract.

title: rotini pasta with vodka
directions: In a large pot, bring 5 quarts of water to a boil. Add salt and cook pasta according to package instructions. On low flame in a large skillet, add butter. Bring to simmer but not burn. Remove skillet from flame while adding vodka, then return to flame. Let vodka evaporate, 1 to 2 minutes, then add Ragu sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook until sauce is heated through. Drain pasta. Pour into skillet with sauce and mix until pasta is well coated. Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine butter, cream of mushroom soup and onion (chopped finely if desired); stir, then add broccoli cuts.
Stir, then sprinkle cheese, grated, and put crushed Ritz crackers, bread crumbs or saltine crumbs on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: o'retha's punch
directions: Dissolve jello and hot water; set aside.
Bring to boil cold water and sugar.
Mix together the two mixtures; cool.
Add pineapple, pineapple juice and ReaLemon.
Freeze.
Set out 2 hours before serving and add the ginger ale.
Serves 50 plus.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes. Cream shortening with
sugars.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with oatmeal mixture.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch loaf cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon-nut bubble bread
directions: Combine sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, yeast and salt.
Mix well. Add eggs, 1/2 cup butter and 2 1/4 cups flour.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining flour, mix well.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic, 5 to 8 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts, 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until doubled in bulk.

title: corn and sausage skillet bake
directions: Cook sausage in a 10-inch skillet until crumbly and well done. Add remaining ingredients, except cornbread mix.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Prepare cornbread mix as directed on box.
Spread evenly on top of corn-sausage mixture.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6. Ummm good!

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat chips and butter.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan; top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars.

title: berry fruit muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make well in center. Beat together with remaining ingredients (except berries) and pour into well.
Blend the ingredients, stirring gently, then add berries.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and lard together well.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together and add to flour mixture.
Refrigerate at least 20 minutes.
Yield: 2 crusts.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 dressing mix in bottom of baking dish (we use a 9 x 13-inch pan).
Melt butter and pour over dressing.
Add chicken or turkey (whichever you prefer).
Cover with remaining stuffing. Mix can of cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup and broth together and pour over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mae's sauerkraut
directions: Brown crumbled sausage; drain off fat.
Add chopped or diced onion.
Add chopped or diced apple and caraway seed.
Heat on medium-low to low heat for about 1 hour or more, if desired. Cover saucepan.

title: microwaving chateau-spiced brandy
directions: In medium bowl, combine sugar, water, cloves, orange slices and cinnamon sticks.
Microwave at High for 8 minutes or until boiling.
Strain into punch bowl.
Stir in wine.
Garnish with additional cinnamon sticks and orange slices.
Yields 6 cups.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet; add flour, salt and pepper. Slowly add milk and stir until thickened.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Cut baked potatoes into cubes, leaving skins on.
Melt butter in saucepan on low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Add potatoes, salt, pepper, onions, bacon, cheese and chicken base. Cook until heated thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk if soup is too thick.

title: martha washingtons
directions: Mix and cream sugar, oleo, milk and vanilla.
Add nuts; roll into balls.
Use powdered sugar to dip hands into as you roll balls.
Dip into chocolate, one at a time.
Drop onto wax paper and refrigerate.

title: peachy blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Combine milk and butter.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Spread peaches evenly on top. Sprinkle with blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until batter rises through fruit.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: franks 'n beans skillet supper
directions: In skillet, cook bacon and then remove and crumble.
Cut each frankfurter into thirds.
In drippings, brown frankfurters and cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, water, potatoes, green beans and thyme.
Heat, stirring now and then.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Serves 4.

title: caramel pear bars
directions: Drain pears and reserve syrup.
Finely dice pears.
Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar until light.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add 1/2 cup pear syrup.
Stir in pears, raisins and walnuts.

title: banana cow
directions: Combine banana, milk, honey, vanilla and ice in container of blender.
Whirl until smooth.
Pour into two 10 ounce glasses. Garnish with lime wedges.
Great for kid's parties.

title: grandma gage's chicken 'n dressing
directions: Place cooked and deboned chicken in Pyrex dish. Put crumbled cornbread in your chicken broth.
Add eggs, onion, celery and sage.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cook like cornbread.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend the sugar, eggs and oil. Sift and add the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and dash of salt. Add the carrots and nuts (optional). Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes. Decrease heat to 300°. Bake 20 minutes longer.
Use a greased spring-form or Bundt pan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix pickle relish, juice and mayo.
Layer crumbled bread, onion and tomatoes.
Spoon some dressing over.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Crumble bacon on top.
Better when 1 or 2 days old.

title: irish poppy tea bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat sour cream, sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, poppy seed and orange juice until well mixed.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat at low speed until combined.
Spoon batter into pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
After cooling, remove from pan and wrap in plastic and let sit overnight.

title: excellent breakfast bake
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°
for 1 hour.
When done baking, take from oven and leave set 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: In plastic bag place seasonings, cheese, parsley and crumbs. Coat chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Oil a shallow roasting pan. Pour in water and arrange chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with oil and melted margarine.

title: take along linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine to taste in boiling water.
Drain and set aside. Heat olive oil in saucepan and add onion and garlic.
Saute until brown.
Add clams, clam juice and seasonings.
Cook until clams are heated through and toss with pasta.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add eggs one at a time, then dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan at 325°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss cauliflower, carrots, celery, green onions and radishes.
Combine all of the remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables and stir to coat.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: green bean empress
directions: Cook celery in oleo or butter until tender-crisp.
Blend cornstarch with chicken stock, soy sauce, sesame seed and garlic salt.
Cook with celery, stirring constantly, until thickened. Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Spread in a 10 x 14-inch greased and floured pan.
Put a large can of cherry or blueberry pie filling on top.
Spread 6 tablespoons melted butter over top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting.
Serves 16.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Finely crush chocolate wafers and sprinkle in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Position knife if food processor bowl; add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients, processing until smooth.
Add egg and process just until blended.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cake is set.
Let cool on wire rack. Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan and transfer to serving platter.
Garnish with chocolate curls. Serves 12.

title: golden crab cakes
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Add crabmeat and egg yolks.
Stir well.
Shape mixture into eight 3-inch patties.
Dredge patties in flour.
Fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with seafood cocktail sauce and if desired, tartar sauce.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Alternate adding milk and flour to butter, egg, sugar mixture.
Gently add 1 quart blueberries (coated with flour to keep from sinking)Pour into 8 x 12 pan and bake at 400 degrees for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar after removing from oven. Cool and cut.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck with diced onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain hamburger.
Add parsley flakes, Worcestershire sauce, oregano and red pepper to the hamburger.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer at 250° for 1 hour (electric frypan).
Check and add water when necessary.

title: olive cheese snacks
directions: Blend cheese and margarine together until light and fluffy. Add hot pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Stir in flour; mix to form a dough.
Shape around olives, using about 1 teaspoon of dough for each olive.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
On stove, bring Karo, butter, vanilla and brown sugar to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, stir well.
Place in oven for 1 hour.
Stir well every 15 minutes.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Mix mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk until blended.
Stir in drained, flaked tuna, diced cheese and onions (a small amount of the green leaf is colorful).
Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until the quiche tests done (solid when you touch the center).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil sugar and water for 6 minutes.
Let cool.
In large container, combine orange concentrate, pineapple, apricots, cherries, pears, peaches, oranges and sliced bananas.
Mix in cooled sugar water.
Freeze in containers, depending on serving size.
Makes a lot.
Serve icy or thawed completely.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook bacon until crispy.
Crumble into bowl.
Mix mayonnaise with bacon crumbs until thick and creamy.
Set aside.
Clean mushrooms; remove stems.
Fill mushroom caps with bacon mixture. Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 1 to 2 minutes more until melted.
Enjoy!

title: cookie cutter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Chill (not very long, maybe an hour or two). Roll out and cut.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 5 to 6 minutes at 400°.
Let cool on wire rack.
Ice with powdered sugar and milk.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 375°.
Sift dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Add raisins and caraway if desired. Add buttermilk and stir with fork until moist.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead gently until smooth, about 1 minute. Shape into a ball and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten into a 7-inch round.
Press large, floured knife into center of loaf almost through to bottom.
Repeat at right angles.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, bread is done when loaf sounds hollow.
Cool on wire rack. Brush with 1 teaspoon melted butter.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the buttermilk, oil and egg. Pour into a hot and oiled iron skillet.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix all ingredients gently.
On top, put 1 cup crushed Ritz crackers mixed with 1/4 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ice box fruit cake
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk until melted, very slowly.
Mix all chopped ingredients.
Mix coconut and cracker crumbs with hand.
Shape into a roll.
Wrap in wax paper and foil, and keep in fridge.
Yields 4 rolls.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in bite size pieces.
Bake in shallow pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen.
Heat before serving; serve very hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: *If you freeze and defrost zucchini and don't remove water, it will be more moist.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Make ice cream into balls and wrap in plastic wrap and put into freezer.
Using a small oven safe bowl, turning bowl upside down, wrap taco shell over bowl and bake in a 350° oven till golden brown.
Cool. After cooled, remove ice cream from freezer and roll into corn flakes. Place ice cream balls into bowls and add syrup, whip cream and top with cherries.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and sour cream.
Stir in melted butter, eggs and brown sugar until well mixed.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into oat mixture until blended.
Divide into 2 greased 12-cup muffin pans.
Sprinkle with more oats.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix well and spread half of mixture in 12 x 8-inch cake pan. Spread on 2 quarts vanilla ice cream and top with rest of crumbs. Freeze.
When ready to serve, spread on 1 can of cherry or strawberry pie filling.

title: orange chiffon dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add orange rind, orange juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened. Whip Dream Whip; fold into cheese-Jell-O mix.
Pour over crumb crust.
Add reserved crumbs to top.
Chill until firm.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter and press into a long cake pan or Pyrex dish.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and vegetables until melted.
Pour over broccoli mixture into greased baking dish and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: chili hot dish
directions: Brown together the onions, green pepper and ground beef; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain and add corn, lima beans and kidney beans.
Add the catsup.
Heat and serve.

title: pfeffernuesse(a christmas cookie)
directions: Flour may be kneaded in when ready to roll.
Roll out and cut thimble size.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until lightly browned. Eat by the hands full.

title: sauerkraut and macaroni
directions: Cook sauerkraut, bacon and onion until kraut is tender.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well.
Cook stir-fry pork in tablespoon of oil.
Add parsley flakes, pimento, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Mix cornstarch with cup of chicken broth; cook until thickened.
Combine macaroni, sauerkraut mixture and thickened broth.
Heat and eat.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Shred entire zucchini.
Removal of seeds and peeling is optional.
Mix zucchini, egg and sugar together, then add Bisquick.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop spoonfuls of batter onto hot griddle, slightly oiled.
Cook approximately 1 minute on each side.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 3 hours at 300° to 350°.

title: hog cookies
directions: Bring Karo syrup to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Mix
well. Add captain Crunch cereal and stir. Spoon out, let dry and enjoy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch, mix well.
Add water and cook until thick and clear.
Add gelatin.
Let cool; pour half in cooled crust.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over berries in a large bowl and toss slightly to coat and spoon over filling in crust.
Cover with the rest of filling and place in refrigerator to set.
Top with Cool Whip and decorate with a few berries.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

directions: Cream
egg

title: homemade rolls
directions: Combine yeast, water and butter (do not stir). Add sugar. Sift flour. Add eggs and salt; mix thoroughly. Cover and store in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours or overnight. Knead thoroughly. Sprinkle flour; roll out. Cut out and dip each roll in melted butter. Put in pan. Let set in warm place for rising (at least 2 to 3 hours). Bake in hot oven 10 minutes.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Blend the softened cream cheese and milk together.
Add the dried beef, onion, green pepper, pepper and sour cream.
Spread into baking dish and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: ziti and mexican meat sauce
directions: Drain; dice pimentos.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground beef, green pepper and onion, stirring often until meat is browned and pepper and onion are tender.
Stir in water, tomato paste, pimentos and sauce mix over high heat; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar and oil. Add chopped cabbage. Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: tony's shrimp and pasta
directions: Saute shrimp in hot oil over medium high heat for about 4 minutes.
Add vegetables to shrimp and cook until shrimp and vegetables are tender, about 4 minutes more.
Finish with a dash of soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Deglaze pan with sherry. Serve over pasta of choice.
Can also be served as a pasta salad.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, cook and drain broccoli.
Stir in 1/2 stick butter and Velveeta cheese until melted.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Spread on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine reserved liquid, 57 sauce and honey. Pour over chicken.
Bake additional 25 minutes, basting occasionally.
Arrange pineapple over chicken and bake 10 minutes longer.
Drain excess fat from sauce.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Butter baking dish. Pour into buttered pan. Crumble cracker crumbs on top. Melt 1 stick of butter and drizzle on top of cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: no crust pizza
directions: Drain mushrooms, adding water (if necessary) to liquid to equal 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Combine liquid, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add ground chuck, oregano and half the mushrooms; mix lightly.
In a 9-inch pie plate, form a "meat" crust.
Cut the Mozzarella cheese into 8 triangles; layer over meat.
Top with pizza sauce, onion, green pepper and remaining mushrooms.
Dash with oregano. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: crazy crunch(microwave)
directions: Pop the 1 cup popcorn and set aside in very large pan or roaster.
In large glass batter bowl, place all ingredients. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Stir and pour over popcorn.
Stir to mix, then pour out on waxed paper to cool.
Do not use cheap margarine!

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour,
oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating well until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in chips.
For each cookie, drop 1/4 cup of dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread into pumpkin shape.
Add dough to form stem.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 32 large cookies.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Place tortillas on lightly greased baking sheets.
Brush with margarine.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on tortillas. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.
Serve with vanilla frozen yogurt and Kahlua, if desired.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: pop nibblers
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together sugar and syrup cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in popped corn and peanuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool until firm.

title: wassail
directions: Bring ingredients to boil on stove.
Simmer in crock-pot for 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
May be used to baste ribs, chops or chicken as they grill.
Also good on Sloppy Joes.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: frango's
directions: Cream together the sugar and soft butter (not melted) and add eggs.
Cream together.
Melt chocolate chips; pour into sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and mint.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper; let harden, then wrap as desired.

title: rich chocolate cherry bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate bits and nuts. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool completely. Put it on a fancy plate and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: peach and strawberry salad
directions: Thaw
strawberries just a little.
Layer ingredients in a compote:
bananas,	strawberries,
pineapple,
pie filling. Stir when ready to serve.
Easy to prepare, easy to eat and no leftovers to worry about!

title: ellie dessert
directions: Fold dry gelatin powder into whipped cream.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars slowly.
Add beaten egg and flavoring.
Add all dry ingredients sifted together.
Heat waffle iron (not too hot) as for breakfast.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Place sausage in a large, deep skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown.
Drain; crumble and set aside.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Lay crescent rolls flat in the bottom of the pan.
Combine cooked sausage, cheese, eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over crescent rolls.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes until bubbly and rolls are baked.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lemon-fruit dessert (quick)
directions: Use juice of fruits (one can) and mix with pudding mix.
Add fruit; chill and serve.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Mix the peach juice and all the other ingredients together; let come to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
Add the peaches and let stand overnight before serving.

title: salmon roll-ups with cheese sauce
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Separate rolls.
Spread rolls with butter and add about 1 tablespoon salmon mixture.
Roll up, starting with wide end.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with Cheese Sauce.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet.
Stir flour, powder and salt together in bowl.
Using 2 knifes or pastry blender, cut butter into flour mixture.
Stir in milk, forming soft dough.
Roll dough on floured surface to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut rounds with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush tops with milk. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Slice and sweeten berries to taste.
Split each biscuit in half; cover with berries.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with whole berries.

title: one dish meal casserole
directions: Cook meat, salt, onion and green pepper until meat is brown. Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix all together in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer coleslaw
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add dressings to taste.

title: cranberry tea cakes
directions: Line 24 muffin cups with paper liners.
In a medium bowl, combine the butter and brown sugar; mix well.
Beat in the eggs, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend in thoroughly.
Stir in the salt, baking soda and flour alternately with sour cream and cranberry sauce.
Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated oven (350°) 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with Buttermilk Icing.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Eat with crackers or sandwich.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in a large bowl, then add all other ingredients and beat for 1 minute.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 70 minutes.
While warm, prick cake with fork so frosting can drizzle in.

title: aunt liz's beaumont inn corn pudding
directions: Stir into the corn the flour, salt, sugar and butter.
Add eggs to cream and stir into the corn.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Stir from bottom 3 different times while baking.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chopped nuts and raisins.
In separate bowl, mix bananas, oil, eggs, vinegar and vanilla.
Add to flour mix.
Bake in an 8 or 9-inch cake pan, greased, at 400° for 30 minutes or until done. Be careful not to overbake.

title: kentucky bluegrass pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream the margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add flour and mix until it is absorbed.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well after each addition.
Mix corn syrup, salt, vanilla and bourbon into the batter. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Immediately pour into pie crust and bake 40 minutes.
Pie should be set, but not runny.
Remove from oven and let cool about 30 minutes before serving.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread over crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk for 1 to 2 minutes, until well blended (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: caramel pie
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar in skillet on medium heat; when brown add water.
Cook until all hardened particles are melted; set aside.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan, 10 x 4-inch or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Measure butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping the bowl constantly.
Beat 5 minutes on high speed scraping occasionally.
On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour into pan.
Bake 70 to 80 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 20 to 25 minutes; remove from pan.

title: cream drop fudge
directions: Put ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave for approximately 2 minutes, stirring a couple of times. When melted, mix real well and pour in a greased pan. Refrigerate and slice into bite-size pieces.

title: sweet-sour chicken breasts
directions: Toss chicken breasts with flour and garlic salt; brown in heated olive oil.
Add chicken broth; cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
Combine syrup with curry, ginger and cornstarch.
Blend in soy sauce, catsup, vinegar and honey.
Pour over chicken and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes longer, or until barely tender.
Add drained pineapple and pea pods.
Cook 5 minutes longer, or until done.
Arrange chicken with peas and sauce on serving platter.
Sprinkle with green onion slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili-cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses in bowl. Blend well. Add remaining ingredients except chili powder; mix well. Shape into ball.
Coat with chili powder. Chill, wrapped in foil, until firm.

title: jarlsberg chicken
directions: Lightly butter a large baking dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter with oil in large heavy skillet over low heat.
Add chicken and cook until done.
Set aside.
Melt 2 more tablespoons butter.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Arrange broccoli in single layer in bottom of dish.
Season chicken with lemon pepper.
Arrange in single layer over broccoli.
Preheat broiler.
Melt remaining butter.
Whisk in flour, stock and wine.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and stir until melted.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with additional cheese over chicken, if desired.
Broil about 6-inches from heat, about 3 to 5 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: pie crust supreme
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until crumbly. Mix water, vinegar and egg together.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix until it forms a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Will keep for 5 days and makes 3 full pies or 6 shells.
Flour hands when handling dough.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Mix shortening and peanut butter.
Add both sugars and mix well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Stir flour mixture in peanut butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and take up.

title: pepperoni cabbage soup
directions: Heat oil in large pan; saut garlic.
Add pepperoni and cabbage.
Cover with water.
Cover pan and cook on low heat until cabbage is done.
Add Northern beans directly from the can.
While this is cooking, cook macaroni separately as directed on the package.
Add as much as you want to soup.
Add water if needed. Serve with Italian bread.
Delicious.

title: baked cheese casserole
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch squares.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese in a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Have a layer of cheese on top.

title: coconut cookie pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a heavy saucepan. Stir to mix well. Add egg yolks but do not mix yet. Gradually add the milk, stirring the yolks into the mixture with it. Cook over medium heat until pudding begins to thicken. It is important to stir this pudding continually to prevent sticking and scorching. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and coconut cookies. Pour into serving bowl. Top with meringue. Brown in a 350 degree oven. If cookies are over 2 inch in diameter, break them in half. Cookies soften as pudding sets.

title: mom's 1962 "freezo" chili
directions: Put all ingredients together in large pot and cook until meat is done, stirring often.

title: tyler's no chocolate brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine all dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt).
Melt butter; stir in brown sugar and add eggs and vanilla to butter mix.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let stand; when cool, cut in cubes.
Makes 45 cubes.
Served with alot of love.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken; then fill bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook broccoli and put on top of chicken.
Blend these ingredients together mayonnaise, lemon juice and chicken soup.
Cover with American cheese.
Break bread in bowl and add melted butter until moist.
Top casserole with this.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain grease.
Add cream cheese and tomatoes. Serve warm with nacho chips.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl (except oil). Add water and stir to soft consistency. Drop by spoonful into heated medium to medium-high temperature oil in large frying pan. Turn over to brown on other side. When golden brown, remove from oil and drain on paper towels.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Split leeks down the middle and wash under running water. Chop leeks, discarding the green portion.
Mince onion.
Saute onion with leeks in butter until soft.
Add diced potatoes and water to cover.
Simmer 15 minutes, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Puree in blender.
Add milk and reheat or chill to serve cold.
Add salt, pepper, chopped chives if desired.
Makes 4 cups.
